Refactored UPS, PDU and ATS input sections
Consolidated and Released for PAL v12.07.007x

tlpProducts.contactinfo: Software Engineering Tripp Lite 1111 W. 35th St. Chicago, IL 60609
tlpProducts.description: This MIB module defines MIB objects which provide mechanisms for remote management capabilities of Tripp Lite PowerAlert and related software.

tlpDeviceNumDevices.name: tlpDeviceNumDevices
tlpDeviceNumDevices.description: The number of devices that this agent is currently managing.

tlpDeviceTable.name: tlpDeviceTable
tlpDeviceTable.description: A list of device table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpDevicesNumDevices.

tlpDeviceEntry.name: tlpDeviceEntry
tlpDeviceEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular device managed by this agent.

tlpDeviceIndex.name: tlpDeviceIndex
tlpDeviceIndex.description: The table row index for the device.

tlpDeviceRowStatus.name: tlpDeviceRowStatus
tlpDeviceRowStatus.description: Used with table edits to indicate the status of a given row in tlDeviceTable.

tlpDeviceType.name: tlpDeviceType
tlpDeviceType.description: The type of device. One of the appropriate hardware types: ups, pdu, envirosense, etc.

tlpDeviceName.name: tlpDeviceName
tlpDeviceName.description: A user-supplied name for the device.

tlpDeviceID.name: tlpDeviceID
tlpDeviceID.description: A user-supplied ID for the device.

tlpDeviceLocation.name: tlpDeviceLocation
tlpDeviceLocation.description: A user-supplied location for the device.

tlpDeviceRegion.name: tlpDeviceRegion
tlpDeviceRegion.description: A user-supplied region for the device.

tlpDeviceStatus.name: tlpDeviceStatus
tlpDeviceStatus.description: The currently most critical alarm status for the device.

tlpDeviceIdentTable.name: tlpDeviceIdentTable
tlpDeviceIdentTable.description: The identity details of each device in device table. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpDevicesNumDevices.

tlpDeviceIdentEntry.name: tlpDeviceIdentEntry
tlpDeviceIdentEntry.description: An entry containing details for a particular device.

tlpDeviceIdentProtocol.name: tlpDeviceIdentProtocol
tlpDeviceIdentProtocol.description: The Tripplite protocol used to communicate with the device.

tlpDeviceIdentCommPortType.name: tlpDeviceIdentCommPortType
tlpDeviceIdentCommPortType.description: The type of communications port used to connect with the device.

tlpDeviceIdentCommPortName.name: tlpDeviceIdentCommPortName
tlpDeviceIdentCommPortName.description: The name of the communications port.

tlpDeviceIdentFirmwareVersion.name: tlpDeviceIdentFirmwareVersion
tlpDeviceIdentFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware version of the device.

tlpDeviceIdentSerialNum.name: tlpDeviceIdentSerialNum
tlpDeviceIdentSerialNum.description: The serial number of the device.

tlpDeviceIdentDateInstalled.name: tlpDeviceIdentDateInstalled
tlpDeviceIdentDateInstalled.description: The installation date for this device in the format of mm/dd/yyyy.

tlpDeviceIdentHardwareVersion.name: tlpDeviceIdentHardwareVersion
tlpDeviceIdentHardwareVersion.description: The hardware revision of the device. This value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME if not supported by the device.

tlpDeviceIdentCurrentUptime.name: tlpDeviceIdentCurrentUptime
tlpDeviceIdentCurrentUptime.description: The device uptime since its last startup. The format of this value is a comma- delimited string representing days, hours and minutes. For example, the value of 123,4,5 represents 123 days, 4 hours and 5 minutes. This value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME if not supported by the device.

tlpDeviceIdentTotalUptime.name: tlpDeviceIdentTotalUptime
tlpDeviceIdentTotalUptime.description: The cumulative (total) uptime for the device. The format of this value is a comma- delimited string representing days, hours and minutes. For example, the value of 123,4,5 represents 123 days, 4 hours and 5 minutes. This value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME if not supported by the device.

tlpUpsIdentNumUps.name: tlpUpsIdentNumUps
tlpUpsIdentNumUps.description: The number of ups devices that this agent is currently managing.

tlpUpsIdentTable.name: tlpUpsIdentTable
tlpUpsIdentTable.description: The identity details of each ups in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are upss.

tlpUpsIdentEntry.name: tlpUpsIdentEntry
tlpUpsIdentEntry.description: An entry containing details for a particular ups.

tlpUpsIdentNumInputs.name: tlpUpsIdentNumInputs
tlpUpsIdentNumInputs.description: The number of input lines supported by the ups.

tlpUpsIdentNumOutputs.name: tlpUpsIdentNumOutputs
tlpUpsIdentNumOutputs.description: The number of output lines supported by the ups.

tlpUpsIdentNumBypass.name: tlpUpsIdentNumBypass
tlpUpsIdentNumBypass.description: The number of bypass lines supported by the ups.

tlpUpsIdentNumPhases.name: tlpUpsIdentNumPhases
tlpUpsIdentNumPhases.description: The number of phases supported by the ups.

tlpUpsIdentNumOutlets.name: tlpUpsIdentNumOutlets
tlpUpsIdentNumOutlets.description: The number of receptacles supported by the ups.

tlpUpsIdentNumOutletGroups.name: tlpUpsIdentNumOutletGroups
tlpUpsIdentNumOutletGroups.description: The number of receptacle groups supported by the ups.

tlpUpsIdentNumBatteryPacks.name: tlpUpsIdentNumBatteryPacks
tlpUpsIdentNumBatteryPacks.description: The number of battery packs, internal and external combined, supported by the ups.

tlpUpsSupportsTable.name: tlpUpsSupportsTable
tlpUpsSupportsTable.description: The supported details of each ups in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are upss.

tlpUpsSupportsEntry.name: tlpUpsSupportsEntry
tlpUpsSupportsEntry.description: An entry containing supported details for a particular ups.

tlpUpsSupportsEnergywise.name: tlpUpsSupportsEnergywise
tlpUpsSupportsEnergywise.description: Indicates whether the ups supports Cisco EnergyWise.

tlpUpsSupportsRampShed.name: tlpUpsSupportsRampShed
tlpUpsSupportsRampShed.description: Indicates whether the ups supports ramping and shedding.

tlpUpsSupportsOutletGroup.name: tlpUpsSupportsOutletGroup
tlpUpsSupportsOutletGroup.description: Indicates whether the ups supports outlet groups.

tlpUpsSupportsOutletCurrentPower.name: tlpUpsSupportsOutletCurrentPower
tlpUpsSupportsOutletCurrentPower.description: Indicates whether the ups reports individual receptacle current and power measurements. Devices that do not support individual receptacle measurements will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME for tlpUpsOutletCurrent and tlpUpsOutletPower.

tlpUpsSupportsOutletVoltage.name: tlpUpsSupportsOutletVoltage
tlpUpsSupportsOutletVoltage.description: Indicates whether the ups reports individual receptacle voltage measurements. Devices that do not support individual receptacle measurements will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME for tlpUpsOutletVoltage.

tlpUpsDeviceTable.name: tlpUpsDeviceTable
tlpUpsDeviceTable.description: The device details of each ups in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are upss.

tlpUpsDeviceEntry.name: tlpUpsDeviceEntry
tlpUpsDeviceEntry.description: An entry containing device details for a particular ups.

tlpUpsDeviceMainLoadState.name: tlpUpsDeviceMainLoadState
tlpUpsDeviceMainLoadState.description: The current state of the main output of the device.

tlpUpsDeviceMainLoadControllable.name: tlpUpsDeviceMainLoadControllable
tlpUpsDeviceMainLoadControllable.description: Indicates whether or not the main output is controllable, and whether the ups can be turned off and on.

tlpUpsDeviceMainLoadCommand.name: tlpUpsDeviceMainLoadCommand
tlpUpsDeviceMainLoadCommand.description: Reading this value will always return 0. Setting this value to turnOff(1) will turn off the main output of the ups. Setting this value to turnOn(2) will turn on the main output of the ups. Setting this value to cycle(3) will turn off the main output, then turn it back on.

tlpUpsDevicePowerOnDelay.name: tlpUpsDevicePowerOnDelay
tlpUpsDevicePowerOnDelay.description: The configurable delay value, which sets the amount of additional time a given device will wait before it connects to a valid AC source. By default the delay value is set to 0.

tlpUpsDeviceTestDate.name: tlpUpsDeviceTestDate
tlpUpsDeviceTestDate.description: The date of the last self-test run on the ups, in the format YYYY-MM-DD.

tlpUpsDeviceTestResultsStatus.name: tlpUpsDeviceTestResultsStatus
tlpUpsDeviceTestResultsStatus.description: The result of the last self-test run on the ups.

tlpUpsDeviceTemperatureC.name: tlpUpsDeviceTemperatureC
tlpUpsDeviceTemperatureC.description: The ambient temperature at or near the ups casing. Temperature measurements are not supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsDeviceTemperatureF.name: tlpUpsDeviceTemperatureF
tlpUpsDeviceTemperatureF.description: The ambient temperature at or near the ups casing. Temperature measurements are not supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatterySummaryTable.name: tlpUpsBatterySummaryTable
tlpUpsBatterySummaryTable.description: The battery system summary of each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps.

tlpUpsBatterySummaryEntry.name: tlpUpsBatterySummaryEntry
tlpUpsBatterySummaryEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular battery system managed by this agent.

tlpUpsBatteryStatus.name: tlpUpsBatteryStatus
tlpUpsBatteryStatus.description: The indication of the capacity remaining in the UPS system's batteries. A value of batteryNormal indicates that the remaining run-time is greater than tlpUpsConfigLowBattTime. A value of batteryLow indicates that the remaining battery run-time is less than or equal to tlpUpsConfigLowBattTime. A value of batteryDepleted indicates that the UPS will be unable to sustain the present load when and if the utility power is lost (including the possibility that the utility power is currently absent and the UPS is unable to sustain the output).

tlpUpsSecondsOnBattery.name: tlpUpsSecondsOnBattery
tlpUpsSecondsOnBattery.description: If the unit is on battery power, the elapsed time since the UPS last switched to battery power, or the time since the network management subsystem was last restarted, whichever is less. Zero shall be returned if the unit is not on battery power.

tlpUpsEstimatedMinutesRemaining.name: tlpUpsEstimatedMinutesRemaining
tlpUpsEstimatedMinutesRemaining.description: An estimate of the time to battery charge depletion under the present load conditions if the utility power is off and remains off, or if it were to be lost and remain off.

tlpUpsEstimatedChargeRemaining.name: tlpUpsEstimatedChargeRemaining
tlpUpsEstimatedChargeRemaining.description: An estimate of the battery charge remaining expressed as a percent of full charge.

tlpUpsBatteryRunTimeRemaining.name: tlpUpsBatteryRunTimeRemaining
tlpUpsBatteryRunTimeRemaining.description: The run time remaining before batteries are exhausted. If the device does not support run time remaining, then the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryDetailTable.name: tlpUpsBatteryDetailTable
tlpUpsBatteryDetailTable.description: The battery detail of each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps.

tlpUpsBatteryDetailEntry.name: tlpUpsBatteryDetailEntry
tlpUpsBatteryDetailEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular battery system managed by this agent.

tlpUpsBatteryDetailVoltage.name: tlpUpsBatteryDetailVoltage
tlpUpsBatteryDetailVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present battery voltage.

tlpUpsBatteryDetailCapacity.name: tlpUpsBatteryDetailCapacity
tlpUpsBatteryDetailCapacity.description: The estimated remaining battery capacity expressed as a percent of full capacity.

tlpUpsBatteryDetailCharge.name: tlpUpsBatteryDetailCharge
tlpUpsBatteryDetailCharge.description: Denotes the charge state of the battery.

tlpUpsBatteryDetailChargerStatus.name: tlpUpsBatteryDetailChargerStatus
tlpUpsBatteryDetailChargerStatus.description: The status of the battery charger. If the device does not support this value, then the agent will report ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentTable.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentTable
tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentTable.description: The battery identification details for each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by upsIdentNumUps and the number of battery battery packs per each as reported by tlpUpsNumBatteryPacks.

tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentEntry.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentEntry
tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular battery pack managed by this agent.

tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentIndex.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentIndex
tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentIndex.description: The table row index for the ups battery pack.

tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentManufacturer.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentManufacturer
tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentManufacturer.description: The manufacturer of the battery pack. If the device does not support this value, then the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentModel.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentModel
tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentModel.description: The model or device name of the battery pack. If the device does not support this value, then the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentSerialNum.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentSerialNum
tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentSerialNum.description: The serial number of the battery pack. If the device does not support this value, then the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentFirmware.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentFirmware
tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentFirmware.description: The firmware of the battery pack. If the device does not support this value, then the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentSKU.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentSKU
tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentSKU.description: The SKU of the battery pack. If the device does not support this value, then the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigTable.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigTable
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigTable.description: The battery configuration details for each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by upsIdentNumUps and the number of battery battery packs per each as reported by tlpUpsNumBatteryPacks.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigEntry.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigEntry
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular battery pack managed by this agent.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigLocation.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigLocation
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigLocation.description: The location of the battery pack.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigStrings.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigStrings
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigStrings.description: The number of series strings in parallel contained in the battery pack. If the device does not support this value, then the agent will report ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigBatteriesPerStrin.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigBatteriesPerString
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigBatteriesPerStrin.description: The number of battery per each string in the battery pack. If the device does not support this value, then the agent will report ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCellsPerBattery.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCellsPerBattery
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCellsPerBattery.description: The number of cells per battery..

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigNumBatteries.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigNumBatteries
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigNumBatteries.description: The total number of batteries contained in the battery pack. If the device does not support this value, then the agent will report ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCapacityUnits.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCapacityUnits
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCapacityUnits.description: The units of measurement used for tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigDesignCapacity and tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCellCapacity. If supported, this value will report either mAHR(1), amps per hour, or mWhr(1), watts per hour. If the device does not support this value, then the agent will report ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigDesignCapacity.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigDesignCapacity
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigDesignCapacity.description: The theoretical or nominal capacity of the battery pack in the measurement defined by tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCapacityUnits. If the device does not support this value, then the agent will report ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCellCapacity.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCellCapacity
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCellCapacity.description: The capacity of the batteries in the measurement defined by tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigCapacityUnits. If the device does not support this value, then the agent will report ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigMinCellVoltage.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigMinCellVoltage
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigMinCellVoltage.description: The minimum cell voltage for the batteries. If the device does not support this value, then the agent will report ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigMaxCellVoltage.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigMaxCellVoltage
tlpUpsBatteryPackConfigMaxCellVoltage.description: The maximum cell voltage for the batteries. If the device does not support this value, then the agent will report ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailTable.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailTable
tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailTable.description: The details of each battery pack for each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss and battery packs managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps and tlpUpsIdentNumBatteryPacks.

tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailEntry.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailEntry
tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular battery system managed by this agent.

tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailCondition.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailCondition
tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailCondition.description: The condition of the battery. A bad battery should be replaced.

tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailTemperatureC.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailTemperatureC
tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailTemperatureC.description: The ambient temperature at or near the UPS Battery casing.

tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailTemperatureF.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailTemperatureF
tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailTemperatureF.description: The ambient temperature at or near the UPS Battery casing.

tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailAge.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailAge
tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailAge.description: The age of the battery in years. This is equal to the current date minus tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentInstallDate.

tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailLastReplaceDate.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailLastReplaceDate
tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailLastReplaceDate.description: The date when the batteries were last replaced in YYYYMMDD format.

tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailNextReplaceDate.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailNextReplaceDate
tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailNextReplaceDate.description: The date when the batteries should next be replaced in YYYYMMDD format.

tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailCycleCount.name: tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailCycleCount
tlpUpsBatteryPackDetailCycleCount.description: The number of times the battery went into invert mode. This number is incremented by 1 each time the unit goes on battery mode (with the exception of Self Test mode). If the device does not support this value, then the agent will report ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsInputTable.name: tlpUpsInputTable
tlpUpsInputTable.description: The input details of each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps.

tlpUpsInputEntry.name: tlpUpsInputEntry
tlpUpsInputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to all input lines per each ups managed by this agent.

tlpUpsInputLineBads.name: tlpUpsInputLineBads
tlpUpsInputLineBads.description: A count of the number of times the input entered an out-of-tolerance condition as defined by the manufacturer. This count is incremented by one each time the input transitions from zero out-of-tolerance lines to one or more input lines out-of-tolerance. This value is not supported on all units. If the ups does not support this value, then the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsInputNominalVoltage.name: tlpUpsInputNominalVoltage
tlpUpsInputNominalVoltage.description: The nominal value of the input line voltage. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsInputNominalFrequency.name: tlpUpsInputNominalFrequency
tlpUpsInputNominalFrequency.description: The nominal value of the input line frequency. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltage.name: tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltage
tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltage.description: The minimum line voltage allowed before the ups system transfers to battery backup.

tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltageLowerBound.name: tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltageLowerBound
tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltageLowerBound.description: The lower boundary value of tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltageUpperBound.name: tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltageUpperBound
tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltageUpperBound.description: The upper boundary value of tlpUpsInputLowTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltage.name: tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltage
tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltage.description: The maximum line voltage allowed before the ups system transfers to battery backup.

tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltageLowerBound.name: tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltageLowerBound
tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltageLowerBound.description: The lower boundary value of tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound.name: tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound
tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound.description: The upper boundary value of tlpUpsInputHighTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpUpsInputPhaseTable.name: tlpUpsInputPhaseTable
tlpUpsInputPhaseTable.description: The input phase details of each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps and tlpUpsIdentNumPhases.

tlpUpsInputPhaseEntry.name: tlpUpsInputPhaseEntry
tlpUpsInputPhaseEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular input phase managed by this agent.

tlpUpsInputPhaseIndex.name: tlpUpsInputPhaseIndex
tlpUpsInputPhaseIndex.description: The table row index for the ups input phase.

tlpUpsInputPhaseFrequency.name: tlpUpsInputPhaseFrequency
tlpUpsInputPhaseFrequency.description: The present input frequency for a given input line.

tlpUpsInputPhaseVoltage.name: tlpUpsInputPhaseVoltage
tlpUpsInputPhaseVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present input voltage for a given input line.

tlpUpsInputPhaseVoltageMin.name: tlpUpsInputPhaseVoltageMin
tlpUpsInputPhaseVoltageMin.description: The minimum input voltage value since the last reset of this value for a given input line. If any value is written to either tlpUpsInputVoltageMin or tlpUpsInputVoltageMax, both will be reset to their appropriate minimum and maximum values.

tlpUpsInputPhaseVoltageMax.name: tlpUpsInputPhaseVoltageMax
tlpUpsInputPhaseVoltageMax.description: The maximum input voltage value since the last reset of this value for a given input line. If any value is written to either tlpUpsInputVoltageMin or tlpUpsInputVoltageMax, both will be reset to their appropriate minimum and maximum values.

tlpUpsInputPhaseCurrent.name: tlpUpsInputPhaseCurrent
tlpUpsInputPhaseCurrent.description: The magnitude of the present input current.

tlpUpsInputPhasePower.name: tlpUpsInputPhasePower
tlpUpsInputPhasePower.description: The magnitude of the present input true power.

tlpUpsOutputTable.name: tlpUpsOutputTable
tlpUpsOutputTable.description: The output details of each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps.

tlpUpsOutputEntry.name: tlpUpsOutputEntry
tlpUpsOutputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular output line managed by this agent.

tlpUpsOutputSource.name: tlpUpsOutputSource
tlpUpsOutputSource.description: The present source of output power. The enumeration none(2) indicates that there is no source of output power (and therefore no output power), for example, the system has opened the output breaker.

tlpUpsOutputNominalVoltage.name: tlpUpsOutputNominalVoltage
tlpUpsOutputNominalVoltage.description: The nominal value of the output voltage. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsOutputFrequency.name: tlpUpsOutputFrequency
tlpUpsOutputFrequency.description: The present output frequency. The output frequency on most ups devices is common across all output lines. Some ups devices, however, maintain the output frequency per each line. If a common frequency is supported by the ups, then this frequency will contain the common frequency value. If not supported, the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsOutputLineTable.name: tlpUpsOutputLineTable
tlpUpsOutputLineTable.description: The output line details of each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps.

tlpUpsOutputLineEntry.name: tlpUpsOutputLineEntry
tlpUpsOutputLineEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular output line managed by this agent.

tlpUpsOutputLineIndex.name: tlpUpsOutputLineIndex
tlpUpsOutputLineIndex.description: The table row index for the ups output line.

tlpUpsOutputLineVoltage.name: tlpUpsOutputLineVoltage
tlpUpsOutputLineVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present output voltage for a given output line.

tlpUpsOutputLinePercentLoad.name: tlpUpsOutputLinePercentLoad
tlpUpsOutputLinePercentLoad.description: The percentage of the UPS power capacity presently being used on this output line, i.e., the greater of the percent load of true power capacity and the percent load of VA.

tlpUpsOutputLineFrequency.name: tlpUpsOutputLineFrequency
tlpUpsOutputLineFrequency.description: The present output frequency on this output line. The output frequency on most ups devices is common across all output lines. Some ups devices, however, maintain the output frequency per each line. If a per line frequency is supported by the ups, then this frequency value will reports the value of this line. If not supported, the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsBypassTable.name: tlpUpsBypassTable
tlpUpsBypassTable.description: The bypass details of each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps.

tlpUpsBypassEntry.name: tlpUpsBypassEntry
tlpUpsBypassEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to all input lines per each ups managed by this agent.

tlpUpsBypassLineTable.name: tlpUpsBypassLineTable
tlpUpsBypassLineTable.description: The bypass line details of each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps.

tlpUpsBypassLineEntry.name: tlpUpsBypassLineEntry
tlpUpsBypassLineEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular bypass line managed by this agent.

tlpUpsBypassLinePower.name: tlpUpsBypassLinePower
tlpUpsBypassLinePower.description: The present true power conveyed by the bypass.

tlpUpsOutletTable.name: tlpUpsOutletTable
tlpUpsOutletTable.description: The details of each ups outlet in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps.

tlpUpsOutletEntry.name: tlpUpsOutletEntry
tlpUpsOutletEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular outlet managed by this agent.

tlpUpsOutletIndex.name: tlpUpsOutletIndex
tlpUpsOutletIndex.description: The table row index for the ups outlet.

tlpUpsOutletName.name: tlpUpsOutletName
tlpUpsOutletName.description: A user-definable string identifying the name of the outlet.

tlpUpsOutletDescription.name: tlpUpsOutletDescription
tlpUpsOutletDescription.description: A user-definable string identifying the device(s) connected to the given outlet.

tlpUpsOutletState.name: tlpUpsOutletState
tlpUpsOutletState.description: The current state of the outlet.

tlpUpsOutletControllable.name: tlpUpsOutletControllable
tlpUpsOutletControllable.description: Denotes whether this outlet is controllable.

tlpUpsOutletCommand.name: tlpUpsOutletCommand
tlpUpsOutletCommand.description: Reading this value will always return 0. Setting this value to turnOff(1) will turn off the outlet. Setting this value to turnOn(2) will turn on the outlet. Setting this value to cycle(3) will turn the outlet off, then turn it back on.

tlpUpsOutletVoltage.name: tlpUpsOutletVoltage
tlpUpsOutletVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present output voltage for a given outlet. If the voltage measurement is not supported for an individual receptacle regardless whether device-wide or just for this receptacle, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. Device-wide support for receptacle voltage measurements is denoted by tlpUpsSupportsOutletVoltage.

tlpUpsOutletCurrent.name: tlpUpsOutletCurrent
tlpUpsOutletCurrent.description: The present output current, in hundreths of amps, of a given outlet. If the current measurement is not supported for an individual receptacle regardless whether device-wide or just for this receptacle, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. Device-wide support for receptacle current measurements is denoted by tlpUpsSupportsCurrentPower.

tlpUpsOutletPower.name: tlpUpsOutletPower
tlpUpsOutletPower.description: The output power of a given outlet. If the power measurement is not supported for an individual receptacle regardless whether device-wide or just for this receptacle, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. Device-wide support for receptacle power measurements is denoted by tlpUpsSupportsCurrentPower.

tlpUpsOutletRampAction.name: tlpUpsOutletRampAction
tlpUpsOutletRampAction.description: The ramp action to take on a given outlet when powering on the device. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpUpsOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsOutletRampDelay.name: tlpUpsOutletRampDelay
tlpUpsOutletRampDelay.description: The number of seconds to delay before powering on the given outlet. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpUpsOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsOutletShedAction.name: tlpUpsOutletShedAction
tlpUpsOutletShedAction.description: The shed action to take on a given outlet when powering off the device. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpUpsOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsOutletShedDelay.name: tlpUpsOutletShedDelay
tlpUpsOutletShedDelay.description: The number of seconds to delay before powering off the given outlet. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpUpsOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsOutletGroup.name: tlpUpsOutletGroup
tlpUpsOutletGroup.description: The tlpUpsOutletGroupIndex group index of the respective group to which the given outlet is assigned, or zero (0) if the given outlet is not grouped.

tlpUpsOutletGroupTable.name: tlpUpsOutletGroupTable
tlpUpsOutletGroupTable.description: The receptacle grouping details of each ups in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the value of tlpUpsIdentNumOutletGroups per each device.

tlpUpsOutletGroupEntry.name: tlpUpsOutletGroupEntry
tlpUpsOutletGroupEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular outlet group managed by this agent.

tlpUpsOutletGroupIndex.name: tlpUpsOutletGroupIndex
tlpUpsOutletGroupIndex.description: The table row index for the ups outlet group.

tlpUpsOutletGroupName.name: tlpUpsOutletGroupName
tlpUpsOutletGroupName.description: The name of this outlet group.

tlpUpsOutletGroupDescription.name: tlpUpsOutletGroupDescription
tlpUpsOutletGroupDescription.description: A description for this outlet group.

tlpUpsOutletGroupState.name: tlpUpsOutletGroupState
tlpUpsOutletGroupState.description: The current state of the outlet group. This value will report off(1) if all outlets in the group are off, on(2) if all outlets in the group are on, mixed(3) if some outlets in the group are off and others are on, or unknown(0) if the state of the outlets cannot be determined.

tlpUpsOutletGroupCommand.name: tlpUpsOutletGroupCommand
tlpUpsOutletGroupCommand.description: Reading this value will always return 0. Setting this value to turnOff(1) will turn off every outlet associated with the group. Setting this value to turnOn(2) will turn on every outlet associated with the group. Setting this value to cycle(3) will turn off every outlet associated with the group, then turn each outlet back on.

tlpUpsWatchdogTable.name: tlpUpsWatchdogTable
tlpUpsWatchdogTable.description: The watchdog details of each ups in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are upss.

tlpUpsWatchdogEntry.name: tlpUpsWatchdogEntry
tlpUpsWatchdogEntry.description: An entry containing watchdog details for a particular ups.

tlpUpsWatchdogSupported.name: tlpUpsWatchdogSupported
tlpUpsWatchdogSupported.description: Indicates whether or not this ups supports a watchdog reboot.

tlpUpsWatchdogSecsBeforeReboot.name: tlpUpsWatchdogSecsBeforeReboot
tlpUpsWatchdogSecsBeforeReboot.description: The maximum number of seconds that can expire between polls that the engine makes to the ups for data. If this time runs out, then the ups will cycle its outputs. Set this to zero to turns disable this feature.

tlpUpsControlTable.name: tlpUpsControlTable
tlpUpsControlTable.description: The actionable controls for each ups in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are upss.

tlpUpsControlEntry.name: tlpUpsControlEntry
tlpUpsControlEntry.description: An entry containing controls for a particular ups.

tlpUpsControlSelfTest.name: tlpUpsControlSelfTest
tlpUpsControlSelfTest.description: Set to TRUE to initiate a self test on the ups.

tlpUpsControlRamp.name: tlpUpsControlRamp
tlpUpsControlRamp.description: Set to TRUE to initiate the pre-designated ramp sequence on the ups.

tlpUpsControlShed.name: tlpUpsControlShed
tlpUpsControlShed.description: Set to TRUE to initiate the pre-designated shed sequence on the ups.

tlpUpsControlUpsOn.name: tlpUpsControlUpsOn
tlpUpsControlUpsOn.description: Set to TRUE to turn the ups on.

tlpUpsControlUpsOff.name: tlpUpsControlUpsOff
tlpUpsControlUpsOff.description: Set to TRUE to turn the ups off.

tlpUpsControlUpsReboot.name: tlpUpsControlUpsReboot
tlpUpsControlUpsReboot.description: Set to TRUE to reboot the ups.

tlpUpsControlBypass.name: tlpUpsControlBypass
tlpUpsControlBypass.description: This switches the ups in and out of bypass mode. This value returns the current bypass mode: disable(0) if the ups is not in bypass mode, enable(1) if the ups is in bypass mode. Set to disable(0) to exit bypass mode, or enable(1) to enter bypass mode. If switching bypass mode is not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigTable.name: tlpUpsConfigTable
tlpUpsConfigTable.description: The configuration details of each ups in the device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of upss managed by the agent as reported by tlpUpsIdentNumUps.

tlpUpsConfigEntry.name: tlpUpsConfigEntry
tlpUpsConfigEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to all input lines per each ups managed by this agent.

tlpUpsConfigInputVoltage.name: tlpUpsConfigInputVoltage
tlpUpsConfigInputVoltage.description: The nominal value of the input line voltage. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. This value may not be writable on all models. If not writable, the value will be rejected and an appropriate error message will be returned.

tlpUpsConfigInputFrequency.name: tlpUpsConfigInputFrequency
tlpUpsConfigInputFrequency.description: The nominal input frequency. On those systems which support read-write access to this object, if there is an attempt to set this variable to a value that is not supported, the request must be rejected and the agent shall respond with an appropriate error message, i.e., badValue for SNMPv1, or inconsistentValue for SNMPv2.

tlpUpsConfigOutputVoltage.name: tlpUpsConfigOutputVoltage
tlpUpsConfigOutputVoltage.description: The nominal value of the output voltage. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, the agent reports ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. This value may not be writable on all models. If not writable, the value will be rejected and an appropriate error message will be returned.

tlpUpsConfigOutputFrequency.name: tlpUpsConfigOutputFrequency
tlpUpsConfigOutputFrequency.description: The nominal output frequency. On those systems which support read-write access to this object, if there is an attempt to set this variable to a value that is not supported, the request will be rejected and the agent will respond with an appropriate error message.

tlpUpsConfigAudibleStatus.name: tlpUpsConfigAudibleStatus
tlpUpsConfigAudibleStatus.description: The requested state of the audible alarm. When in the disabled state, the audible alarm should never sound. The enabled state is self- describing. Setting this object to muted(3) when the audible alarm is sounding shall temporarily silence the alarm. It will remain muted until it would normally stop sounding and the value returned for read operations during this period shall equal muted(3). At the end of this period, the value shall revert to enabled(2). Writes of the value muted(3) when the audible alarm is not sounding shall be accepted but otherwise shall have no effect.

tlpUpsConfigAutoBatteryTest.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoBatteryTest
tlpUpsConfigAutoBatteryTest.description: When disabled(0), the ups will not perform an automatic battery selftest. When set to another value, the ups will perform an automatic selftest in the approximate period defined by each respective enumerated value. This feature is generally not recommended.

tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartAfterShutdown.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartAfterShutdown
tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartAfterShutdown.description: When enabled(1), the ups should autorestart after a shutdown from battery mode if valid AC is applied. When disabled(0), the ups should not autorestart when AC is restored and instead power up into standby mode.

tlpUpsConfigAutoRampOnTransition.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoRampOnTransition
tlpUpsConfigAutoRampOnTransition.description: When enabled(1), the ups should perform its preconfigured ramp sequence when valid AC is restored while in battery mode. If this value is not supported by the ups, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigAutoShedOnTransition.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoShedOnTransition
tlpUpsConfigAutoShedOnTransition.description: When enabled(1), the ups should perform its preconfigured shed sequence when valid AC is lost causing the ups to enter battery mode. If this value is not supported by the ups, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigBypassLowerLimitPercent.name: tlpUpsConfigBypassLowerLimitPercent
tlpUpsConfigBypassLowerLimitPercent.description: The lowest AC input voltage allowed to be output to the load while in bypass mode. This setting is expressed as a percentage from nominal voltage. If this value is not supported by the ups, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigBypassUpperLimitPercent.name: tlpUpsConfigBypassUpperLimitPercent
tlpUpsConfigBypassUpperLimitPercent.description: The highest AC input voltage allowed to be output to the load while in bypass mode. This setting is expressed as a percentage from nominal voltage. If this value is not supported by the ups, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigBypassLowerLimitVoltage.name: tlpUpsConfigBypassLowerLimitVoltage
tlpUpsConfigBypassLowerLimitVoltage.description: The lowest AC input voltage allowed to be output to the load while in bypass mode. If this value is not supported by the ups, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigBypassUpperLimitVoltage.name: tlpUpsConfigBypassUpperLimitVoltage
tlpUpsConfigBypassUpperLimitVoltage.description: The highest AC input voltage allowed to be output to the load while in bypass mode. If this value is not supported by the ups, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigColdStart.name: tlpUpsConfigColdStart
tlpUpsConfigColdStart.description: This option enables or disables the ability to turn the ups on without AC supplied. If this value is not supported by the ups, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigEconomicMode.name: tlpUpsConfigEconomicMode
tlpUpsConfigEconomicMode.description: The configurable economic mode options for the ups. The online(0) mode is the default configuration of most upss, which is synonymous as having the economic mode disabled. The economy(1) mode is the typical configuration to run in economy mode, which is synonymous as having the economic mode enabled. Constant50Hz(2) is a power strategy, which fixes the output frequency at 50Hz. Constant60Hz(3) is a power stragegy, which fixes the output frequency at 60Hz. ConstantAuto(4) regulates the output frequency at nominal input frequency. AutoAdaptive(5) mode will cause the ups to automatically switch between online(0), maximum quality, and economy(1), maximum efficiency, to improve efficiency during stable utility periods and improve output regulation during unstable utility periods. Not all values are supported by all upss. Most upss, if supportive of economic mode, only supports online(0) and economy(1). If the ups does not support economic mode, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigFaultAction.name: tlpUpsConfigFaultAction
tlpUpsConfigFaultAction.description: Determines the action to take if the output needs to be shut down due to a fault condition, limited by the type of fault incurred. When configured for bypass(0), the ups will go to bypass on a fault condition. When configured for standby(1), the ups will go to standby mode on a fault condition. Either configuration will be valid as long as AC input is within normal line voltage and frequency limits when the fault condition occurs. If the line is outside these limits, the ups will turn off. If this value is not supported by the ups, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigOffMode.name: tlpUpsConfigOffMode
tlpUpsConfigOffMode.description: This option governs what mode the ups should go into when AC input is available, but the load is either off or not battery backed up. If this setting is configured for bypass(1), the intention is that any time the ups would normally go into standby mode, it would instead go into bypass mode. Note that this setting does not dictate the mode for fault conditions, which is governed by tlpUpsConfigFaultAction. If this value is not supported by the ups, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigLineSensitivity.name: tlpUpsConfigLineSensitivity
tlpUpsConfigLineSensitivity.description: Adjusts the AC line voltage sensitivity setting. If this value is not supported by the ups, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartTable.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartTable
tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartTable.description: The configurable automatic restart options of each ups in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are upss. Not all options are available on all upss.

tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartEntry.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartEntry
tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartEntry.description: An entry containing configurable automatic restart options for a particular ups.

tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartInverterShutdown.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartInverterShutdown
tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartInverterShutdown.description: If enabled(1) and the ups is turned off from invert mode (via user interaction), if line becomes valid, the ups will automatically go to line mode. If disabled(0), the ups will turn back on and go to standby mode instead.

tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartDelayedWakeup.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartDelayedWakeup
tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartDelayedWakeup.description: If enabled(1) and power fails during a DelayBeforeStartup and line remains invalid after the timeout expires, the ups will be set to turn back on automatically. If disabled(0), the ups will turn back on and go to standby mode instead.

tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartLowVoltageCutoff.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartLowVoltageCutoff
tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartLowVoltageCutoff.description: If enabled(1) and the ups is turned off from invert mode (via low voltage cutoff), if line becomes valid, the ups will automatically go to line mode. If disabled(0), the ups will turn back on and go to standby mode instead.

tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartOverLoad.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartOverLoad
tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartOverLoad.description: If enabled(1) and the ups is turned off from invert mode (via overload), if line becomes valid, the ups will automatically go to line mode. If disabled(0), the ups will turn back on and go to standby mode instead.

tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartOverTemperature.name: tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartOverTemperature
tlpUpsConfigAutoRestartOverTemperature.description: If enabled(1) and the ups is turned off from invert mode (via over temperature), if line becomes valid, the ups will automatically go to line mode. If disabled(0), the ups will turn back on and go to standby mode instead.

tlpUpsConfigThresholdTable.name: tlpUpsConfigThresholdTable
tlpUpsConfigThresholdTable.description: The configurable threshold options of each ups in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are upss. Not all options are available on all upss.

tlpUpsConfigThresholdEntry.name: tlpUpsConfigThresholdEntry
tlpUpsConfigThresholdEntry.description: An entry containing configurable threshold options for a particular ups.

tlpUpsConfigBatteryAgeThreshold.name: tlpUpsConfigBatteryAgeThreshold
tlpUpsConfigBatteryAgeThreshold.description: The number of months for a battery to be in service. The battery age alarm, tlpUpsAlarmBatteryAgeAboveThreshold, is triggered when the current date exceeds tlpUpsBatteryPackIdentInstallDate by tlpUpsConfigBatteryAgeThreshold months.

tlpUpsConfigLowBatteryThreshold.name: tlpUpsConfigLowBatteryThreshold
tlpUpsConfigLowBatteryThreshold.description: This value denotes the percentage of battery capacity remaining warning level. The low battery alarm, tlpUpsAlarmLowBattery, is triggered when tlpUpsEstimatedChargeRemaining drops below this value.

tlpUpsConfigLowBatteryTime.name: tlpUpsConfigLowBatteryTime
tlpUpsConfigLowBatteryTime.description: The value in seconds of tlpUpsEstimatedMinutesRemaining at which a lowBattery condition is declared. For agents which support only discrete (discontinuous) values, then the agent shall round up to the next supported value. If the requested value is larger than the largest supported value, then the largest supported value shall be selected.

tlpUpsConfigOverLoadThreshold.name: tlpUpsConfigOverLoadThreshold
tlpUpsConfigOverLoadThreshold.description: This value denotes the percentage of load at which the overload condition occurs. The overload alarm, tlpUpsAlarmOutputOverload, is triggered when the percentage of output load exceeds this value.

tlpPduIdentNumPdu.name: tlpPduIdentNumPdu
tlpPduIdentNumPdu.description: The number of pdu devices that this agent is currently managing.

tlpPduIdentTable.name: tlpPduIdentTable
tlpPduIdentTable.description: The identity details of each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are pdus.

tlpPduIdentEntry.name: tlpPduIdentEntry
tlpPduIdentEntry.description: An entry containing details for a particular pdu.

tlpPduIdentNumInputs.name: tlpPduIdentNumInputs
tlpPduIdentNumInputs.description: The number of input lines supported by the pdu.

tlpPduIdentNumOutputs.name: tlpPduIdentNumOutputs
tlpPduIdentNumOutputs.description: The number of output lines supported by the pdu.

tlpPduIdentNumPhases.name: tlpPduIdentNumPhases
tlpPduIdentNumPhases.description: The number of phases supported by the pdu.

tlpPduIdentNumOutlets.name: tlpPduIdentNumOutlets
tlpPduIdentNumOutlets.description: The number of receptacles supported by the pdu.

tlpPduIdentNumOutletGroups.name: tlpPduIdentNumOutletGroups
tlpPduIdentNumOutletGroups.description: The number of receptacle groups supported by the pdu.

tlpPduIdentNumCircuits.name: tlpPduIdentNumCircuits
tlpPduIdentNumCircuits.description: The number of circuits supported by the pdu.

tlpPduIdentNumBreakers.name: tlpPduIdentNumBreakers
tlpPduIdentNumBreakers.description: The number of bank breakers supported by the pdu.

tlpPduIdentNumHeatsinks.name: tlpPduIdentNumHeatsinks
tlpPduIdentNumHeatsinks.description: The number of heatsink thermistors supported by the pdu.

tlpPduSupportsTable.name: tlpPduSupportsTable
tlpPduSupportsTable.description: The supported details of each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are pdus.

tlpPduSupportsEntry.name: tlpPduSupportsEntry
tlpPduSupportsEntry.description: An entry containing supported details for a particular pdu.

tlpPduSupportsEnergywise.name: tlpPduSupportsEnergywise
tlpPduSupportsEnergywise.description: Indicates whether the pdu supports Cisco EnergyWise.

tlpPduSupportsRampShed.name: tlpPduSupportsRampShed
tlpPduSupportsRampShed.description: Indicates whether the pdu supports ramping and shedding.

tlpPduSupportsOutletGroup.name: tlpPduSupportsOutletGroup
tlpPduSupportsOutletGroup.description: Indicates whether the pdu supports outlet groups.

tlpPduSupportsOutletCurrentPower.name: tlpPduSupportsOutletCurrentPower
tlpPduSupportsOutletCurrentPower.description: Indicates whether the pdu reports individual receptacle current and power measurements. Devices that do not support individual receptacle measurements will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME for tlpPduOutletCurrent and tlpPduOutletPower.

tlpPduSupportsOutletVoltage.name: tlpPduSupportsOutletVoltage
tlpPduSupportsOutletVoltage.description: Indicates whether the pdu reports individual receptacle voltage measurements. Devices that do not support individual receptacle measurements will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME for tlpPduOutletVoltage.

tlpPduDisplayTable.name: tlpPduDisplayTable
tlpPduDisplayTable.description: The display details of each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are pdus.

tlpPduDisplayEntry.name: tlpPduDisplayEntry
tlpPduDisplayEntry.description: An entry containing display details for a particular pdu.

tlpPduDisplayScheme.name: tlpPduDisplayScheme
tlpPduDisplayScheme.description: Indicates the display scheme of the LED display. The value schemeReverse(0) indicates the tricolor LED indicator uses an alternate pattern. The value schemeNormal(1) indicates the LED indicator uses the standard pattern. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, the value will always return schemeNormal(1).

tlpPduDisplayOrientation.name: tlpPduDisplayOrientation
tlpPduDisplayOrientation.description: Indicates the physical orientation of the LED display. The value displayNormal(0) indicates the display is right-side-up (normal). The value displayReverse(1) indicates the display is upside-down. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, the value will always return displayNormal(0).

tlpPduDisplayAutoScroll.name: tlpPduDisplayAutoScroll
tlpPduDisplayAutoScroll.description: Indicates whether the LED display automatically scrolls through displaying status values.

tlpPduDisplayIntensity.name: tlpPduDisplayIntensity
tlpPduDisplayIntensity.description: Indicates the intensity, as a percentage, of the LED display. The value intensity100(4) indicates the display is at 100% intensity. The other values indicate the display is at a lesser intensity based upon the respective percentage denoted.

tlpPduDisplayUnits.name: tlpPduDisplayUnits
tlpPduDisplayUnits.description: Indicates the units of measurement displayed on the LED display. The value normal(0) indicates that a temperature value, for example, is displayed in degrees Farenheit. The value metric(1) indicates a temperature value is displayed in degrees Celsius.

tlpPduDeviceTable.name: tlpPduDeviceTable
tlpPduDeviceTable.description: The device details of each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are pdus.

tlpPduDeviceEntry.name: tlpPduDeviceEntry
tlpPduDeviceEntry.description: An entry containing device details for a particular pdu.

tlpPduDeviceMainLoadState.name: tlpPduDeviceMainLoadState
tlpPduDeviceMainLoadState.description: The current state of the main output of the device.

tlpPduDeviceMainLoadControllable.name: tlpPduDeviceMainLoadControllable
tlpPduDeviceMainLoadControllable.description: Indicates whether or not the main output is controllable, and whether the ups can be turned off and on.

tlpPduDeviceMainLoadCommand.name: tlpPduDeviceMainLoadCommand
tlpPduDeviceMainLoadCommand.description: Reading this value will always return 0. Setting this value to turnOff(1) will turn off the main output of the ups. Setting this value to turnOn(2) will turn on the main output of the ups. Setting this value to cycle(3) will turn off the main output, then turn it back on.

tlpPduDevicePowerOnDelay.name: tlpPduDevicePowerOnDelay
tlpPduDevicePowerOnDelay.description: The configurable delay value, which sets the amount of additional time a given device will wait before it connects to a valid AC source. By default the delay value is set to 0. For devices with multiple AC input sources, this delay only applies to the primary input source.

tlpPduDeviceTotalInputPowerRating.name: tlpPduDeviceTotalInputPowerRating
tlpPduDeviceTotalInputPowerRating.description: The total input power rating of all phases on the device. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpPduDeviceTemperatureC.name: tlpPduDeviceTemperatureC
tlpPduDeviceTemperatureC.description: The ambient temperature at or near the PDU casing. Temperature measurements are not supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpPduDeviceTemperatureF.name: tlpPduDeviceTemperatureF
tlpPduDeviceTemperatureF.description: The ambient temperature at or near the PDU casing. Temperature measurements are not supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpPduDevicePhaseImbalance.name: tlpPduDevicePhaseImbalance
tlpPduDevicePhaseImbalance.description: The percentage of imbalance of the three phases. This value is in the range from 0% imbalance to 100% imbalance. The lower the value, the better balanced the phases are. If all load is on a single phase, the imbalance is defined as 100%.

tlpPduDeviceOutputPowerTotal.name: tlpPduDeviceOutputPowerTotal
tlpPduDeviceOutputPowerTotal.description: The AC output total power for all circuits.

tlpPduDeviceAggregatePowerFactor.name: tlpPduDeviceAggregatePowerFactor
tlpPduDeviceAggregatePowerFactor.description: The aggregrate power factor of all phases.

tlpPduDeviceOutputCurrentPrecision.name: tlpPduDeviceOutputCurrentPrecision
tlpPduDeviceOutputCurrentPrecision.description: Output current is reported by tlpPduOutputCurrent, tlpPduOutputCurrentMin and tlpPduOutputCurrentMax. These values are all reported in hundredths (0.01A), which accommodates all models; however, on any given device the actual precision may vary. This value describes the actual precision, which can be used as a divisor against the output current values to obtain the true output current measurement. For example, if tlpPduOutputCurrent reports 530 and tlpPduDeviceOutputCurrentPrecision is tenths(1), then the actual output current is 5.3.

tlpPduInputTable.name: tlpPduInputTable
tlpPduInputTable.description: The input details of each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of pdus managed by the agent as reported by tlpPduIdentNumPdus.

tlpPduInputEntry.name: tlpPduInputEntry
tlpPduInputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular pdu managed by this agent.

tlpPduInputNominalVoltage.name: tlpPduInputNominalVoltage
tlpPduInputNominalVoltage.description: The nominal value of the input line voltage. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpPduInputNominalVoltagePhaseToPhase.name: tlpPduInputNominalVoltagePhaseToPhase
tlpPduInputNominalVoltagePhaseToPhase.description: The nominal value of the input line voltage as measured from phase to phase. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return zero.

tlpPduInputNominalVoltagePhaseToNeutral.name: tlpPduInputNominalVoltagePhaseToNeutral
tlpPduInputNominalVoltagePhaseToNeutral.description: The nominal value of the input line voltage as measured from phase to neutral. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return zero.

tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltage.name: tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltage
tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltage.description: The minimum line voltage allowed before the unit disconnects the AC input connection. This value may not be writable on all models. If not writable, the value will be rejected and an appropriate error message will be returned. When supported, the minimum and maximum values allowed are dictated by tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltageLowerBound and tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltageUpperBound respectively.

tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltageLowerBound.name: tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltageLowerBound
tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltageLowerBound.description: The lower boundary value of tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltageUpperBound.name: tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltageUpperBound
tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltageUpperBound.description: The upper boundary value of tlpPduInputLowTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltage.name: tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltage
tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltage.description: The maximum line voltage allowed before the unit disconnects the AC input connection. This value may not be writable on all models. If not writable, the value will be rejected and an appropriate error message will be returned. When supported, the minimum and maximum values allowed are dictated by tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltageLowerBound and tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound respectively.

tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltageLowerBound.name: tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltageLowerBound
tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltageLowerBound.description: The lower boundary value of tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound.name: tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound
tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound.description: The upper boundary value of tlpPduInputHighTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpPduInputCurrentLimit.name: tlpPduInputCurrentLimit
tlpPduInputCurrentLimit.description: The capacity of each phase conductor in the pdu limited by the AC input cord or any other potential limiting factors unique to a given unit.

tlpPduInputPhaseTable.name: tlpPduInputPhaseTable
tlpPduInputPhaseTable.description: The input phase details of each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the value of tlpPduIdentNumInputs and tlpPduIdentNumPhases per each device.

tlpPduInputPhaseEntry.name: tlpPduInputPhaseEntry
tlpPduInputPhaseEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular input phase managed by this agent.

tlpPduInputPhaseIndex.name: tlpPduInputPhaseIndex
tlpPduInputPhaseIndex.description: The table row index for the pdu phase.

tlpPduInputPhasePhaseType.name: tlpPduInputPhasePhaseType
tlpPduInputPhasePhaseType.description: Denotes whether measurements are phase to neutral(0) or phase to phase(1).

tlpPduInputPhaseFrequency.name: tlpPduInputPhaseFrequency
tlpPduInputPhaseFrequency.description: The present input frequency for a given phase.

tlpPduInputPhaseVoltage.name: tlpPduInputPhaseVoltage
tlpPduInputPhaseVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present input voltage for a given phase.

tlpPduInputPhaseVoltageMin.name: tlpPduInputPhaseVoltageMin
tlpPduInputPhaseVoltageMin.description: The minimum input voltage value since the last reset of this value for a given phase. If any value is written to either tlpPduInputVoltageMin or tlpPduInputVoltageMax, both will be reset to their appropriate minimum and maximum values.

tlpPduInputPhaseVoltageMax.name: tlpPduInputPhaseVoltageMax
tlpPduInputPhaseVoltageMax.description: The maximum input voltage value since the last reset of this value for a given phase. If any value is written to either tlpPduInputVoltageMin or tlpPduInputVoltageMax, both will be reset to their appropriate minimum and maximum values.

tlpPduInputPhaseCurrent.name: tlpPduInputPhaseCurrent
tlpPduInputPhaseCurrent.description: The magnitude of the present input current for a given phase.

tlpPduOutputTable.name: tlpPduOutputTable
tlpPduOutputTable.description: The output details of each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the value of tlpPduIdentNumOutputs per each device.

tlpPduOutputEntry.name: tlpPduOutputEntry
tlpPduOutputEntry.description: An entry containing output information applicable to a particular phase managed by this agent.

tlpPduOutputIndex.name: tlpPduOutputIndex
tlpPduOutputIndex.description: The table row index for the pdu phase.

tlpPduOutputPhase.name: tlpPduOutputPhase
tlpPduOutputPhase.description: Indicates the phase associated with the output line.

tlpPduOutputPhaseType.name: tlpPduOutputPhaseType
tlpPduOutputPhaseType.description: Denotes whether measurements are phase to neutral(0) or phase to phase(1).

tlpPduOutputVoltage.name: tlpPduOutputVoltage
tlpPduOutputVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present output voltage for a given output line.

tlpPduOutputCurrent.name: tlpPduOutputCurrent
tlpPduOutputCurrent.description: The output current, in hundreths of amps, for a given phase.

tlpPduOutputCurrentMin.name: tlpPduOutputCurrentMin
tlpPduOutputCurrentMin.description: The minimum current observed for a given phase since last reset.

tlpPduOutputCurrentMax.name: tlpPduOutputCurrentMax
tlpPduOutputCurrentMax.description: The maximum current observed for a given phase since last reset.

tlpPduOutputActivePower.name: tlpPduOutputActivePower
tlpPduOutputActivePower.description: The output power for a given phase.

tlpPduOutputPowerFactor.name: tlpPduOutputPowerFactor
tlpPduOutputPowerFactor.description: The output power factor, in hundreths of a percent, for a given phase.

tlpPduOutputSource.name: tlpPduOutputSource
tlpPduOutputSource.description: The present source of output power. The enumeration none(0) indicates that there is no source of output power (and therefore no output power), for example, the system has opened the output breaker.

tlpPduOutletTable.name: tlpPduOutletTable
tlpPduOutletTable.description: The receptacle status details of each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the value of tlpPduIdentNumOutlets per each device.

tlpPduOutletEntry.name: tlpPduOutletEntry
tlpPduOutletEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular outlet managed by this agent.

tlpPduOutletIndex.name: tlpPduOutletIndex
tlpPduOutletIndex.description: The table row index for the pdu outlet.

tlpPduOutletName.name: tlpPduOutletName
tlpPduOutletName.description: A user-definable string identifying the name of the outlet.

tlpPduOutletDescription.name: tlpPduOutletDescription
tlpPduOutletDescription.description: A user-definable string identifying the device(s) connected to the given outlet.

tlpPduOutletState.name: tlpPduOutletState
tlpPduOutletState.description: The current state of the outlet.

tlpPduOutletControllable.name: tlpPduOutletControllable
tlpPduOutletControllable.description: Denotes whether this outlet is controllable.

tlpPduOutletCommand.name: tlpPduOutletCommand
tlpPduOutletCommand.description: Reading this value will always return 0. Setting this value to turnOff(1) will turn off the outlet. Setting this value to turnOn(2) will turn on the outlet. Setting this value to cycle(3) will turn the outlet off, then turn it back on.

tlpPduOutletVoltage.name: tlpPduOutletVoltage
tlpPduOutletVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present output voltage for a given outlet. If the voltage measurement is not supported for an individual receptacle regardless whether device-wide or just for this receptacle, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. Device-wide support for receptacle voltage measurements is denoted by tlpPduSupportsOutletVoltage.

tlpPduOutletCurrent.name: tlpPduOutletCurrent
tlpPduOutletCurrent.description: The present output current, in hundreths of amps, of a given outlet. If the current measurement is not supported for an individual receptacle regardless whether device-wide or just for this receptacle, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. Device-wide support for receptacle current measurements is denoted by tlpPduSupportsCurrentPower.

tlpPduOutletPower.name: tlpPduOutletPower
tlpPduOutletPower.description: The output power of a given outlet. If the power measurement is not supported for an individual receptacle regardless whether device-wide or just for this receptacle, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. Device-wide support for receptacle power measurements is denoted by tlpPduSupportsCurrentPower.

tlpPduOutletRampAction.name: tlpPduOutletRampAction
tlpPduOutletRampAction.description: The ramp action to take on a given outlet when powering on the device. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpPduOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpPduOutletRampDelay.name: tlpPduOutletRampDelay
tlpPduOutletRampDelay.description: The number of seconds to delay before powering on the given outlet. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpPduOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpPduOutletShedAction.name: tlpPduOutletShedAction
tlpPduOutletShedAction.description: The shed action to take on a given outlet when powering off the device. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpPduOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpPduOutletShedDelay.name: tlpPduOutletShedDelay
tlpPduOutletShedDelay.description: The number of seconds to delay before powering off the given outlet. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpPduOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpPduOutletGroup.name: tlpPduOutletGroup
tlpPduOutletGroup.description: The tlpPduOutletGroupIndex group index of the respective group to which the given outlet is assigned, or zero (0) if the given outlet is not grouped.

tlpPduOutletBank.name: tlpPduOutletBank
tlpPduOutletBank.description: Indicates on which bank the given outlet is located.

tlpPduOutletCircuit.name: tlpPduOutletCircuit
tlpPduOutletCircuit.description: Indicates on which circuit the given outlet is wired.

tlpPduOutletPhase.name: tlpPduOutletPhase
tlpPduOutletPhase.description: Indicates on which phase or phases the given outlet is associated. For single phase devices, this object will always return phase1(1). For 3-phase devices with outlets wired to a single phase, this object will return phase1(1), phase2(2) or phase3(3). For 3-phase devices with outlets wired to two phases, this object will return phase1-2(4) for phases 1 and 2, phase2-3(5) for phases 2 and 3, and phase3-1(6) for phases 3 and 1. Devices that do not report phase connections will return unknown(0).

tlpPduOutletGroupTable.name: tlpPduOutletGroupTable
tlpPduOutletGroupTable.description: The receptacle grouping details of each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the value of tlpPduIdentNumOutletGroups per each device.

tlpPduOutletGroupEntry.name: tlpPduOutletGroupEntry
tlpPduOutletGroupEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular outlet group managed by this agent.

tlpPduOutletGroupIndex.name: tlpPduOutletGroupIndex
tlpPduOutletGroupIndex.description: The table row index for the pdu outlet group.

tlpPduOutletGroupName.name: tlpPduOutletGroupName
tlpPduOutletGroupName.description: The name of this outlet group.

tlpPduOutletGroupDescription.name: tlpPduOutletGroupDescription
tlpPduOutletGroupDescription.description: A description for this outlet group.

tlpPduOutletGroupState.name: tlpPduOutletGroupState
tlpPduOutletGroupState.description: The current state of the outlet group. This value will report off(1) if all outlets in the group are off, on(2) if all outlets in the group are on, mixed(3) if some outlets in the group are off and others are on, or unknown(0) if the state of the outlets cannot be determined.

tlpPduOutletGroupCommand.name: tlpPduOutletGroupCommand
tlpPduOutletGroupCommand.description: Reading this value will always return 0. Setting this value to turnOff(1) will turn off every outlet associated with the group. Setting this value to turnOn(2) will turn on every outlet associated with the group. Setting this value to cycle(3) will turn off every outlet associated with the group, then turn each outlet back on.

tlpPduCircuitTable.name: tlpPduCircuitTable
tlpPduCircuitTable.description: A list of pdu circuit table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpPduIdentNumCircuits.

tlpPduCircuitEntry.name: tlpPduCircuitEntry
tlpPduCircuitEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular circuit managed by this agent.

tlpPduCircuitIndex.name: tlpPduCircuitIndex
tlpPduCircuitIndex.description: The table row index for the pdu circuit.

tlpPduCircuitPhase.name: tlpPduCircuitPhase
tlpPduCircuitPhase.description: Indicates on which phase or phases the given circuit is wired. For single phase devices, this object will always return phase1(1). For 3-phase devices with outlets wired to a single phase, this object will return phase1(1), phase2(2) or phase3(3). For 3-phase devices with outlets wired to two phases, this object will return phase1-2(4) for phases 1 and 2, phase2-3(5) for phases 2 and 3, and phase3-1(6) for phases 3 and 1. Devices that do not report phase connections will return unknown(0).

tlpPduCircuitInputVoltage.name: tlpPduCircuitInputVoltage
tlpPduCircuitInputVoltage.description: The input voltage for a circuit.

tlpPduCircuitTotalCurrent.name: tlpPduCircuitTotalCurrent
tlpPduCircuitTotalCurrent.description: The total current for all receptacles in a given circuit.

tlpPduCircuitCurrentLimit.name: tlpPduCircuitCurrentLimit
tlpPduCircuitCurrentLimit.description: The current capacity of a circuit in the system limited by the circuit breaker or wiring used in a given unit.

tlpPduCircuitCurrentMin.name: tlpPduCircuitCurrentMin
tlpPduCircuitCurrentMin.description: The minimum total current for all receptacles in a given circuit since last reset.

tlpPduCircuitCurrentMax.name: tlpPduCircuitCurrentMax
tlpPduCircuitCurrentMax.description: The maximum total current for all receptacles in a given circuit since last reset.

tlpPduCircuitTotalPower.name: tlpPduCircuitTotalPower
tlpPduCircuitTotalPower.description: The total power for all receptacles in a given circuit.

tlpPduCircuitPowerFactor.name: tlpPduCircuitPowerFactor
tlpPduCircuitPowerFactor.description: The power factor for all receptacles in a given circuit.

tlpPduCircuitUtilization.name: tlpPduCircuitUtilization
tlpPduCircuitUtilization.description: The percentage of utilization of a given circuit. This is typically a calculation of tlpPduCircuitTotalCurrent / tlpPduCircuitCurrentLimit.

tlpPduBreakerTable.name: tlpPduBreakerTable
tlpPduBreakerTable.description: A list of pdu bank breaker table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpPduIdentNumBreakers.

tlpPduBreakerEntry.name: tlpPduBreakerEntry
tlpPduBreakerEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular bank breaker managed by this agent.

tlpPduBreakerIndex.name: tlpPduBreakerIndex
tlpPduBreakerIndex.description: The table row index for the pdu bank breaker.

tlpPduBreakerStatus.name: tlpPduBreakerStatus
tlpPduBreakerStatus.description: Indicates whether the bank breaker is open(0), closed(1) or not installed(2).

tlpPduHeatsinkTable.name: tlpPduHeatsinkTable
tlpPduHeatsinkTable.description: A list of pdu heatsink thermistor table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpPduIdentNumHeatsinks.

tlpPduHeatsinkEntry.name: tlpPduHeatsinkEntry
tlpPduHeatsinkEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular heatsink thermistor managed by this agent.

tlpPduHeatsinkIndex.name: tlpPduHeatsinkIndex
tlpPduHeatsinkIndex.description: The table row index for the pdu heatsink thermistor.

tlpPduHeatsinkStatus.name: tlpPduHeatsinkStatus
tlpPduHeatsinkStatus.description: Indicates whether the heatsink thermistor is available. The entry will return notAvailable(0) if a thermistor is either non-existent or disconnected, or available(1) when connected.

tlpPduHeatsinkTemperatureC.name: tlpPduHeatsinkTemperatureC
tlpPduHeatsinkTemperatureC.description: The temperature at the heatsink termistor in tenths degrees Centigrade. Heatsink temperature measurements are not supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpPduHeatsinkTemperatureF.name: tlpPduHeatsinkTemperatureF
tlpPduHeatsinkTemperatureF.description: The temperature at the heatsink termistor in tenths degrees Farenheit. Heatsink temperature measurements are not supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpPduControlTable.name: tlpPduControlTable
tlpPduControlTable.description: The actionable controls for each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are pdus.

tlpPduControlEntry.name: tlpPduControlEntry
tlpPduControlEntry.description: An entry containing controls for a particular pdu.

tlpPduControlRamp.name: tlpPduControlRamp
tlpPduControlRamp.description: Set to TRUE to initiate the pre-designated ramp sequence on the pdu.

tlpPduControlShed.name: tlpPduControlShed
tlpPduControlShed.description: Set to TRUE to initiate the pre-designated shed sequence on the pdu.

tlpPduControlPduOn.name: tlpPduControlPduOn
tlpPduControlPduOn.description: Set to TRUE to turn the pdu on.

tlpPduControlPduOff.name: tlpPduControlPduOff
tlpPduControlPduOff.description: Set to TRUE to turn the pdu off.

tlpPduControlPduReboot.name: tlpPduControlPduReboot
tlpPduControlPduReboot.description: Set to TRUE to reboot the pdu.

tlpPduConfigTable.name: tlpPduConfigTable
tlpPduConfigTable.description: The configuration options of each pdu in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are pdus. Not all options are available on all pdus.

tlpPduConfigEntry.name: tlpPduConfigEntry
tlpPduConfigEntry.description: An entry containing configuration options for a particular pdu.

tlpPduConfigInputVoltage.name: tlpPduConfigInputVoltage
tlpPduConfigInputVoltage.description: The nominal value of the input line voltage. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. This value may not be writable on all models. If not writable, the value will be rejected and an appropriate error message will be returned.

tlpEnvIdentNumEnvirosense.name: tlpEnvIdentNumEnvirosense
tlpEnvIdentNumEnvirosense.description: The number of envirosense devices that this agent is currently managing.

tlpEnvIdentTable.name: tlpEnvIdentTable
tlpEnvIdentTable.description: The identity details of each envirosense in device table. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpDevicesNumDevices.

tlpEnvIdentEntry.name: tlpEnvIdentEntry
tlpEnvIdentEntry.description: An entry containing details for a particular envirosense.

tlpEnvIdentTempSupported.name: tlpEnvIdentTempSupported
tlpEnvIdentTempSupported.description: Indicates whether or not temperature is supported.

tlpEnvIdentHumiditySupported.name: tlpEnvIdentHumiditySupported
tlpEnvIdentHumiditySupported.description: Indicates whether or not temperature is supported.

tlpEnvNumInputContacts.name: tlpEnvNumInputContacts
tlpEnvNumInputContacts.description: The number of input contacts supported by the envirosense.

tlpEnvNumOutputContacts.name: tlpEnvNumOutputContacts
tlpEnvNumOutputContacts.description: The number of output contacts supported by the envirosense.

tlpEnvTemperatureTable.name: tlpEnvTemperatureTable
tlpEnvTemperatureTable.description: The temperature details of each envirosense in device table. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpDevicesNumDevices.

tlpEnvTemperatureEntry.name: tlpEnvTemperatureEntry
tlpEnvTemperatureEntry.description: An entry containing temperature details for a particular envirosense.

tlpEnvTemperatureInAlarm.name: tlpEnvTemperatureInAlarm
tlpEnvTemperatureInAlarm.description: Indicates whether or not temperature is in alarm.

tlpEnvHumidityTable.name: tlpEnvHumidityTable
