tlpEnvHumidityTable.description: The humidity details of each envirosense in device table. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpDevicesNumDevices.

tlpEnvHumidityEntry.name: tlpEnvHumidityEntry
tlpEnvHumidityEntry.description: An entry containing humidity details for a particular envirosense.

tlpEnvHumidityInAlarm.name: tlpEnvHumidityInAlarm
tlpEnvHumidityInAlarm.description: Indicates whether or not humidity is in alarm.

tlpEnvInputContactTable.name: tlpEnvInputContactTable
tlpEnvInputContactTable.description: The input contact details of each envirosense in device table. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpDevicesNumDevices.

tlpEnvInputContactEntry.name: tlpEnvInputContactEntry
tlpEnvInputContactEntry.description: An entry containing input contact details for a particular envirosense.

tlpEnvInputContactIndex.name: tlpEnvInputContactIndex
tlpEnvInputContactIndex.description: The table row index for the envirosense input contact details.

tlpEnvInputContactName.name: tlpEnvInputContactName
tlpEnvInputContactName.description: The name or description of the contact.

tlpEnvInputContactNormalState.name: tlpEnvInputContactNormalState
tlpEnvInputContactNormalState.description: The normal operating position of the contact.

tlpEnvInputContactCurrentState.name: tlpEnvInputContactCurrentState
tlpEnvInputContactCurrentState.description: The current state of the contact.

tlpEnvInputContactInAlarm.name: tlpEnvInputContactInAlarm
tlpEnvInputContactInAlarm.description: Indicates whether or not the contact is in alarm.

tlpEnvOutputContactTable.name: tlpEnvOutputContactTable
tlpEnvOutputContactTable.description: The output contact details of each envirosense in device table. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpDevicesNumDevices.

tlpEnvOutputContactEntry.name: tlpEnvOutputContactEntry
tlpEnvOutputContactEntry.description: An entry containing output contact details for a particular envirosense.

tlpEnvOutputContactIndex.name: tlpEnvOutputContactIndex
tlpEnvOutputContactIndex.description: The table row index for the envirosense output contact details.

tlpEnvOutputContactName.name: tlpEnvOutputContactName
tlpEnvOutputContactName.description: The name or description of the contact.

tlpEnvOutputContactNormalState.name: tlpEnvOutputContactNormalState
tlpEnvOutputContactNormalState.description: The normal operating position of the contact.

tlpEnvOutputContactCurrentState.name: tlpEnvOutputContactCurrentState
tlpEnvOutputContactCurrentState.description: The current state of the contact.

tlpEnvOutputContactInAlarm.name: tlpEnvOutputContactInAlarm
tlpEnvOutputContactInAlarm.description: Indicates whether or not the contact is in alarm.

tlpEnvConfigTable.name: tlpEnvConfigTable
tlpEnvConfigTable.description: The configuration options of each envirosense in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are envirosenses. Not all options are available on all envirosenses.

tlpEnvConfigEntry.name: tlpEnvConfigEntry
tlpEnvConfigEntry.description: An entry containing configuration options for a particular envirosenses.

tlpEnvTemperatureLowLimit.name: tlpEnvTemperatureLowLimit
tlpEnvTemperatureLowLimit.description: The lower alarm limit for ambient temperature.

tlpEnvTemperatureHighLimit.name: tlpEnvTemperatureHighLimit
tlpEnvTemperatureHighLimit.description: The upper alarm limit for ambient temperature.

tlpEnvHumidityLowLimit.name: tlpEnvHumidityLowLimit
tlpEnvHumidityLowLimit.description: The lower alarm limit for ambient humidity.

tlpEnvHumidityHighLimit.name: tlpEnvHumidityHighLimit
tlpEnvHumidityHighLimit.description: The upper alarm limit for ambient humidity.

tlpAtsIdentNumAts.name: tlpAtsIdentNumAts
tlpAtsIdentNumAts.description: The number of ats devices that this agent is currently managing.

tlpAtsIdentTable.name: tlpAtsIdentTable
tlpAtsIdentTable.description: The identity details of each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are atss.

tlpAtsIdentEntry.name: tlpAtsIdentEntry
tlpAtsIdentEntry.description: An entry containing details for a particular ats.

tlpAtsIdentNumInputs.name: tlpAtsIdentNumInputs
tlpAtsIdentNumInputs.description: The number of inputs supported by the ats.

tlpAtsIdentNumOutputs.name: tlpAtsIdentNumOutputs
tlpAtsIdentNumOutputs.description: The number of outputs supported by the ats.

tlpAtsIdentNumPhases.name: tlpAtsIdentNumPhases
tlpAtsIdentNumPhases.description: The number of phases per input supported by the ats.

tlpAtsIdentNumOutlets.name: tlpAtsIdentNumOutlets
tlpAtsIdentNumOutlets.description: The number of receptacles supported by the ats.

tlpAtsIdentNumOutletGroups.name: tlpAtsIdentNumOutletGroups
tlpAtsIdentNumOutletGroups.description: The number of receptacle groups supported by the ats.

tlpAtsIdentNumCircuits.name: tlpAtsIdentNumCircuits
tlpAtsIdentNumCircuits.description: The number of circuits supported by the ats.

tlpAtsIdentNumBreakers.name: tlpAtsIdentNumBreakers
tlpAtsIdentNumBreakers.description: The number of bank breakers supported by the ats.

tlpAtsIdentNumHeatsinks.name: tlpAtsIdentNumHeatsinks
tlpAtsIdentNumHeatsinks.description: The number of heatsink thermistors supported by the ats.

tlpAtsSupportsTable.name: tlpAtsSupportsTable
tlpAtsSupportsTable.description: The supported details of each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are atss.

tlpAtsSupportsEntry.name: tlpAtsSupportsEntry
tlpAtsSupportsEntry.description: An entry containing supported details for a particular ats.

tlpAtsSupportsEnergywise.name: tlpAtsSupportsEnergywise
tlpAtsSupportsEnergywise.description: Indicates whether the ats supports Cisco EnergyWise.

tlpAtsSupportsRampShed.name: tlpAtsSupportsRampShed
tlpAtsSupportsRampShed.description: Indicates whether the ats supports ramping and shedding.

tlpAtsSupportsOutletGroup.name: tlpAtsSupportsOutletGroup
tlpAtsSupportsOutletGroup.description: Indicates whether the ats supports outlet groups.

tlpAtsSupportsOutletCurrentPower.name: tlpAtsSupportsOutletCurrentPower
tlpAtsSupportsOutletCurrentPower.description: Indicates whether the ats reports individual receptacle current and power measurements. Devices that do not support individual receptacle measurements will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME for tlpAtsOutletCurrent and tlpAtsOutletPower.

tlpAtsSupportsOutletVoltage.name: tlpAtsSupportsOutletVoltage
tlpAtsSupportsOutletVoltage.description: Indicates whether the ats reports individual receptacle voltage measurements. Devices that do not support individual receptacle measurements will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME for tlpAtsOutletVoltage.

tlpAtsDisplayTable.name: tlpAtsDisplayTable
tlpAtsDisplayTable.description: The display details of each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are atss.

tlpAtsDisplayEntry.name: tlpAtsDisplayEntry
tlpAtsDisplayEntry.description: An entry containing display details for a particular ats.

tlpAtsDisplayScheme.name: tlpAtsDisplayScheme
tlpAtsDisplayScheme.description: Indicates the display scheme of the LED display. The value schemeReverse(0) indicates the tricolor LED indicator uses an alternate pattern. The value schemeNormal(1) indicates the LED indicator uses the standard pattern. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, the value will always return schemeNormal(1).

tlpAtsDisplayOrientation.name: tlpAtsDisplayOrientation
tlpAtsDisplayOrientation.description: Indicates the physical orientation of the LED display. The value displayNormal(0) indicates the display is right-side-up (normal). The value displayReverse(1) indicates the display is upside-down. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, the value will always return displayNormal(0).

tlpAtsDisplayAutoScroll.name: tlpAtsDisplayAutoScroll
tlpAtsDisplayAutoScroll.description: Indicates whether the LED display automatically scrolls through displaying status values.

tlpAtsDisplayIntensity.name: tlpAtsDisplayIntensity
tlpAtsDisplayIntensity.description: Indicates the intensity, as a percentage, of the LED display. The value intensity100(4) indicates the display is at 100% intensity. The other values indicate the display is at a lesser intensity based upon the respective percentage denoted.

tlpAtsDisplayUnits.name: tlpAtsDisplayUnits
tlpAtsDisplayUnits.description: Indicates the units of measurement displayed on the LED display. The value normal(0) indicates that a temperature value, for example, is displayed in degrees Farenheit. The value metric(1) indicates a temperature value is displayed in degrees Celsius.

tlpAtsDeviceTable.name: tlpAtsDeviceTable
tlpAtsDeviceTable.description: The device details of each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are atss.

tlpAtsDeviceEntry.name: tlpAtsDeviceEntry
tlpAtsDeviceEntry.description: An entry containing device details for a particular ats.

tlpAtsDeviceMainLoadState.name: tlpAtsDeviceMainLoadState
tlpAtsDeviceMainLoadState.description: The current state of the main output of the device.

tlpAtsDeviceMainLoadControllable.name: tlpAtsDeviceMainLoadControllable
tlpAtsDeviceMainLoadControllable.description: Indicates whether or not the main output is controllable, and whether the ups can be turned off and on.

tlpAtsDeviceMainLoadCommand.name: tlpAtsDeviceMainLoadCommand
tlpAtsDeviceMainLoadCommand.description: Reading this value will always return 0. Setting this value to turnOff(1) will turn off the main output of the ups. Setting this value to turnOn(2) will turn on the main output of the ups. Setting this value to cycle(3) will turn off the main output, then turn it back on.

tlpAtsDevicePowerOnDelay.name: tlpAtsDevicePowerOnDelay
tlpAtsDevicePowerOnDelay.description: The configurable delay value, which sets the amount of additional time a given device will wait before it connects to a valid AC source. By default the delay value is set to 0. For devices with multiple AC input sources, this delay only applies to the primary input source.

tlpAtsDeviceTotalInputPowerRating.name: tlpAtsDeviceTotalInputPowerRating
tlpAtsDeviceTotalInputPowerRating.description: The total input power rating of all phases on the device. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsDeviceTemperatureC.name: tlpAtsDeviceTemperatureC
tlpAtsDeviceTemperatureC.description: The ambient temperature at or near the ats casing. Temperature measurements are not supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsDeviceTemperatureF.name: tlpAtsDeviceTemperatureF
tlpAtsDeviceTemperatureF.description: The ambient temperature at or near the ats casing. Temperature measurements are not supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsDevicePhaseImbalance.name: tlpAtsDevicePhaseImbalance
tlpAtsDevicePhaseImbalance.description: The percentage of imbalance of the three phases. This value is in the range from 0% imbalance to 100% imbalance. The lower the value, the better balanced the phases are. If all load is on a single phase, the imbalance is defined as 100%.

tlpAtsDeviceOutputPowerTotal.name: tlpAtsDeviceOutputPowerTotal
tlpAtsDeviceOutputPowerTotal.description: The AC output total power for all circuits.

tlpAtsDeviceAggregatePowerFactor.name: tlpAtsDeviceAggregatePowerFactor
tlpAtsDeviceAggregatePowerFactor.description: The aggregrate power factor of all phases.

tlpAtsDeviceOutputCurrentPrecision.name: tlpAtsDeviceOutputCurrentPrecision
tlpAtsDeviceOutputCurrentPrecision.description: Output current is reported by tlpAtsOutputCurrent, tlpAtsOutputCurrentMin and tlpAtsOutputCurrentMax. These values are all reported in hundredths (0.01A), which accommodates all models; however, on any given device the actual precision may vary. This value describes the actual precision, which can be used as a divisor against the output current values to obtain the true output current measurement. For example, if tlpAtsOutputCurrent reports 530 and tlpAtsDeviceOutputCurrentPrecision is tenths(1), then the actual output current is 5.3.

tlpAtsDeviceGeneralFault.name: tlpAtsDeviceGeneralFault
tlpAtsDeviceGeneralFault.description: Indicates whether or not the ats is in a system fault condition. When the ats is in such a fault condition, the condition can be cleared with tlpAtsControlResetGeneralFault.

tlpAtsInputTable.name: tlpAtsInputTable
tlpAtsInputTable.description: The input details of each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the number of atss managed by the agent as reported by tlpAtsIdentNumAts.

tlpAtsInputEntry.name: tlpAtsInputEntry
tlpAtsInputEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular primary input phase managed by this agent.

tlpAtsInputNominalVoltage.name: tlpAtsInputNominalVoltage
tlpAtsInputNominalVoltage.description: The nominal value of the input line voltage. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsInputNominalVoltagePhaseToPhase.name: tlpAtsInputNominalVoltagePhaseToPhase
tlpAtsInputNominalVoltagePhaseToPhase.description: The nominal value of the input line voltage as measured from phase to phase. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return zero.

tlpAtsInputNominalVoltagePhaseToNeutral.name: tlpAtsInputNominalVoltagePhaseToNeutral
tlpAtsInputNominalVoltagePhaseToNeutral.description: The nominal value of the input line voltage as measured from phase to neutral. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return zero.

tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltage.name: tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltage
tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltage.description: The minimum line voltage allowed before the unit disconnects the AC input connection.

tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltageLowerBound.name: tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltageLowerBound
tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltageLowerBound.description: The lower boundary value of tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltageUpperBound.name: tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltageUpperBound
tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltageUpperBound.description: The upper boundary value of tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltage.name: tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltage
tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltage.description: The maximum line voltage allowed before the unit disconnects the AC input connection.

tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltageLowerBound.name: tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltageLowerBound
tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltageLowerBound.description: The lower boundary value of tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound.name: tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound
tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound.description: The upper boundary value of tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltage as dictated by the hardware of the unit.

tlpAtsInputFairVoltageThreshold.name: tlpAtsInputFairVoltageThreshold
tlpAtsInputFairVoltageThreshold.description: The voltage level at which the device will transition between sources.

tlpAtsInputBadVoltageThreshold.name: tlpAtsInputBadVoltageThreshold
tlpAtsInputBadVoltageThreshold.description: The minimum line voltage allowed before the device disconnects the AC input connection.

tlpAtsInputSourceAvailability.name: tlpAtsInputSourceAvailability
tlpAtsInputSourceAvailability.description: The determination as to which of two AC input lines are available. The agent will return either inputSourceA(1) or inputSourceB(2) if only one line is available, or inputSourceAB(3) if both lines are available. The agent will never return none(0) since the device will be powered off if neither line is available.

tlpAtsInputSourceInUse.name: tlpAtsInputSourceInUse
tlpAtsInputSourceInUse.description: The determination as to which one of two AC input lines is in use. Not all devices support the reporting of which source is currently in use. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsInputSourceTransitionCount.name: tlpAtsInputSourceTransitionCount
tlpAtsInputSourceTransitionCount.description: The number of times the device transitions between primary and secondary sources. Most devices are limied to 65533 transitions, after which the value will not increment. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsInputCurrentLimit.name: tlpAtsInputCurrentLimit
tlpAtsInputCurrentLimit.description: The capacity of each phase conductor in the ats limited by the AC input cord or any other potential limiting factors unique to a given unit. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsInputPhaseTable.name: tlpAtsInputPhaseTable
tlpAtsInputPhaseTable.description: The input phase details of each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the value of tlpAtsIdentNumInputs and tlpAtsIdentNumPhases per each device.

tlpAtsInputPhaseEntry.name: tlpAtsInputPhaseEntry
tlpAtsInputPhaseEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular primary input phase managed by this agent.

tlpAtsInputLineIndex.name: tlpAtsInputLineIndex
tlpAtsInputLineIndex.description: The table row index for the input line on the ats.

tlpAtsInputPhaseIndex.name: tlpAtsInputPhaseIndex
tlpAtsInputPhaseIndex.description: The table row index for the input phase for the input line.

tlpAtsInputPhaseType.name: tlpAtsInputPhaseType
tlpAtsInputPhaseType.description: Denotes whether measurements are phase to neutral(0) or phase to phase(1).

tlpAtsInputPhaseFrequency.name: tlpAtsInputPhaseFrequency
tlpAtsInputPhaseFrequency.description: The present input frequency for a given phase.

tlpAtsInputPhaseVoltage.name: tlpAtsInputPhaseVoltage
tlpAtsInputPhaseVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present input voltage for a given phase.

tlpAtsInputPhaseVoltageMin.name: tlpAtsInputPhaseVoltageMin
tlpAtsInputPhaseVoltageMin.description: The minimum input voltage value since the last reset of this value for a given phase. If any value is written to either tlpAtsInputVoltageMin or tlpAtsInputVoltageMax, both will be reset to their appropriate minimum and maximum values.

tlpAtsInputPhaseVoltageMax.name: tlpAtsInputPhaseVoltageMax
tlpAtsInputPhaseVoltageMax.description: The maximum input voltage value since the last reset of this value for a given phase. If any value is written to either tlpAtsInputVoltageMin or tlpAtsInputVoltageMax, both will be reset to their appropriate minimum and maximum values.

tlpAtsInputPhaseCurrent.name: tlpAtsInputPhaseCurrent
tlpAtsInputPhaseCurrent.description: The magnitude of the present input current for a given phase.

tlpAtsOutputTable.name: tlpAtsOutputTable
tlpAtsOutputTable.description: The output details of each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the value of tlpAtsIdentNumOutputs per each device.

tlpAtsOutputEntry.name: tlpAtsOutputEntry
tlpAtsOutputEntry.description: An entry containing output information applicable to a particular phase managed by this agent.

tlpAtsOutputIndex.name: tlpAtsOutputIndex
tlpAtsOutputIndex.description: The table row index for the ats phase.

tlpAtsOutputPhase.name: tlpAtsOutputPhase
tlpAtsOutputPhase.description: Indicates the phase associated with the output line.

tlpAtsOutputPhaseType.name: tlpAtsOutputPhaseType
tlpAtsOutputPhaseType.description: Denotes whether measurements are phase to neutral(0) or phase to phase(1).

tlpAtsOutputVoltage.name: tlpAtsOutputVoltage
tlpAtsOutputVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present output voltage for a given output line.

tlpAtsOutputCurrent.name: tlpAtsOutputCurrent
tlpAtsOutputCurrent.description: The output current, in hundreths of amps, for a given phase.

tlpAtsOutputCurrentMin.name: tlpAtsOutputCurrentMin
tlpAtsOutputCurrentMin.description: The minimum current observed for a given phase since last reset.

tlpAtsOutputCurrentMax.name: tlpAtsOutputCurrentMax
tlpAtsOutputCurrentMax.description: The maximum current observed for a given phase since last reset.

tlpAtsOutputActivePower.name: tlpAtsOutputActivePower
tlpAtsOutputActivePower.description: The output power for a given phase.

tlpAtsOutputPowerFactor.name: tlpAtsOutputPowerFactor
tlpAtsOutputPowerFactor.description: The output power factor, in hundreths of a percent, for a given phase.

tlpAtsOutputSource.name: tlpAtsOutputSource
tlpAtsOutputSource.description: The present source of output power. The enumeration none(0) indicates that there is no source of output power (and therefore no output power), for example, the system has opened the output breaker.

tlpAtsOutletTable.name: tlpAtsOutletTable
tlpAtsOutletTable.description: The receptacle status details of each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the value of tlpAtsIdentNumOutlets per each device.

tlpAtsOutletEntry.name: tlpAtsOutletEntry
tlpAtsOutletEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular outlet managed by this agent.

tlpAtsOutletIndex.name: tlpAtsOutletIndex
tlpAtsOutletIndex.description: The table row index for the ats outlet.

tlpAtsOutletName.name: tlpAtsOutletName
tlpAtsOutletName.description: A user-definable string identifying the name of the outlet.

tlpAtsOutletDescription.name: tlpAtsOutletDescription
tlpAtsOutletDescription.description: A user-definable string identifying the device(s) connected to the given outlet.

tlpAtsOutletState.name: tlpAtsOutletState
tlpAtsOutletState.description: The current state of the outlet.

tlpAtsOutletControllable.name: tlpAtsOutletControllable
tlpAtsOutletControllable.description: Denotes whether this outlet is controllable.

tlpAtsOutletCommand.name: tlpAtsOutletCommand
tlpAtsOutletCommand.description: Reading this value will always return 0. Setting this value to turnOff(1) will turn off the outlet. Setting this value to turnOn(2) will turn on the outlet. Setting this value to cycle(3) will turn the outlet off, then turn it back on.

tlpAtsOutletVoltage.name: tlpAtsOutletVoltage
tlpAtsOutletVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present output voltage for a given outlet. If the voltage measurement is not supported for an individual receptacle regardless whether device-wide or just for this receptacle, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. Device-wide support for receptacle voltage measurements is denoted by tlpAtsSupportsOutletVoltage.

tlpAtsOutletCurrent.name: tlpAtsOutletCurrent
tlpAtsOutletCurrent.description: The present output current, in hundreths of amps, of a given outlet. If the current measurement is not supported for an individual receptacle regardless whether device-wide or just for this receptacle, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. Device-wide support for receptacle current measurements is denoted by tlpAtsSupportsCurrentPower.

tlpAtsOutletPower.name: tlpAtsOutletPower
tlpAtsOutletPower.description: The output power of a given outlet. If the power measurement is not supported for an individual receptacle regardless whether device-wide or just for this receptacle, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. Device-wide support for receptacle power measurements is denoted by tlpAtsSupportsCurrentPower.

tlpAtsOutletRampAction.name: tlpAtsOutletRampAction
tlpAtsOutletRampAction.description: The ramp action to take on a given outlet when powering on the device. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpAtsOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsOutletRampDelay.name: tlpAtsOutletRampDelay
tlpAtsOutletRampDelay.description: The number of seconds to delay before powering on the given outlet. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpAtsOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsOutletShedAction.name: tlpAtsOutletShedAction
tlpAtsOutletShedAction.description: The shed action to take on a given outlet when powering off the device. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpAtsOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsOutletShedDelay.name: tlpAtsOutletShedDelay
tlpAtsOutletShedDelay.description: The number of seconds to delay before powering off the given outlet. If this receptacle is not controllable, as denoted by tlpAtsOutletControllable, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsOutletGroup.name: tlpAtsOutletGroup
tlpAtsOutletGroup.description: The tlpAtsOutletGroupIndex group index of the respective group to which the given outlet is assigned, or zero (0) if the given outlet is not grouped.

tlpAtsOutletBank.name: tlpAtsOutletBank
tlpAtsOutletBank.description: Indicates on which bank the given outlet is located.

tlpAtsOutletCircuit.name: tlpAtsOutletCircuit
tlpAtsOutletCircuit.description: Indicates on which circuit the given outlet is wired.

tlpAtsOutletPhase.name: tlpAtsOutletPhase
tlpAtsOutletPhase.description: Indicates on which phase or phases the given outlet is associated. For single phase devices, this object will always return phase1(1). For 3-phase devices with outlets wired to a single phase, this object will return phase1(1), phase2(2) or phase3(3). For 3-phase devices with outlets wired to two phases, this object will return phase1-2(4) for phases 1 and 2, phase2-3(5) for phases 2 and 3, and phase3-1(6) for phases 3 and 1. Devices that do not report phase connections will return unknown(0).

tlpAtsOutletGroupTable.name: tlpAtsOutletGroupTable
tlpAtsOutletGroupTable.description: The receptacle grouping details of each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain the number of entries based upon the value of tlpAtsIdentNumOutletGroups per each device.

tlpAtsOutletGroupEntry.name: tlpAtsOutletGroupEntry
tlpAtsOutletGroupEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular outlet group managed by this agent.

tlpAtsOutletGroupIndex.name: tlpAtsOutletGroupIndex
tlpAtsOutletGroupIndex.description: The table row index for the ats outlet group.

tlpAtsOutletGroupName.name: tlpAtsOutletGroupName
tlpAtsOutletGroupName.description: The name of this outlet group.

tlpAtsOutletGroupDescription.name: tlpAtsOutletGroupDescription
tlpAtsOutletGroupDescription.description: A description for this outlet group.

tlpAtsOutletGroupState.name: tlpAtsOutletGroupState
tlpAtsOutletGroupState.description: The current state of the outlet group. This value will report off(1) if all outlets in the group are off, on(2) if all outlets in the group are on, mixed(3) if some outlets in the group are off and others are on, or unknown(0) if the state of the outlets cannot be determined.

tlpAtsOutletGroupCommand.name: tlpAtsOutletGroupCommand
tlpAtsOutletGroupCommand.description: Reading this value will always return 0. Setting this value to turnOff(1) will turn off every outlet associated with the group. Setting this value to turnOn(2) will turn on every outlet associated with the group. Setting this value to cycle(3) will turn off every outlet associated with the group, then turn each outlet back on.

tlpAtsCircuitTable.name: tlpAtsCircuitTable
tlpAtsCircuitTable.description: A list of ats circuit table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpAtsIdentNumCircuits.

tlpAtsCircuitEntry.name: tlpAtsCircuitEntry
tlpAtsCircuitEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular circuit managed by this agent.

tlpAtsCircuitIndex.name: tlpAtsCircuitIndex
tlpAtsCircuitIndex.description: The table row index for the ats circuit.

tlpAtsCircuitPhase.name: tlpAtsCircuitPhase
tlpAtsCircuitPhase.description: Indicates on which phase or phases the given circuit is wired. For single phase devices, this object will always return phase1(1). For 3-phase devices with outlets wired to a single phase, this object will return phase1(1), phase2(2) or phase3(3). For 3-phase devices with outlets wired to two phases, this object will return phase1-2(4) for phases 1 and 2, phase2-3(5) for phases 2 and 3, and phase3-1(6) for phases 3 and 1. Devices that do not report phase connections will return unknown(0).

tlpAtsCircuitInputVoltage.name: tlpAtsCircuitInputVoltage
tlpAtsCircuitInputVoltage.description: The input voltage for a circuit.

tlpAtsCircuitTotalCurrent.name: tlpAtsCircuitTotalCurrent
tlpAtsCircuitTotalCurrent.description: The total current for all receptacles in a given circuit.

tlpAtsCircuitCurrentLimit.name: tlpAtsCircuitCurrentLimit
tlpAtsCircuitCurrentLimit.description: The current capacity of a circuit in the system limited by the circuit breaker or wiring used in a given unit.

tlpAtsCircuitCurrentMin.name: tlpAtsCircuitCurrentMin
tlpAtsCircuitCurrentMin.description: The minimum total current for all receptacles in a given circuit since last reset.

tlpAtsCircuitCurrentMax.name: tlpAtsCircuitCurrentMax
tlpAtsCircuitCurrentMax.description: The maximum total current for all receptacles in a given circuit since last reset.

tlpAtsCircuitTotalPower.name: tlpAtsCircuitTotalPower
tlpAtsCircuitTotalPower.description: The total power for all receptacles in a given circuit.

tlpAtsCircuitPowerFactor.name: tlpAtsCircuitPowerFactor
tlpAtsCircuitPowerFactor.description: The power factor for all receptacles in a given circuit.

tlpAtsCircuitUtilization.name: tlpAtsCircuitUtilization
tlpAtsCircuitUtilization.description: The percentage of utilization of a given circuit. This is typically a calculation of tlpAtsCircuitTotalCurrent / tlpAtsCircuitCurrentLimit.

tlpAtsBreakerTable.name: tlpAtsBreakerTable
tlpAtsBreakerTable.description: A list of ats bank breaker table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpAtsIdentNumBreakers.

tlpAtsBreakerEntry.name: tlpAtsBreakerEntry
tlpAtsBreakerEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular bank breaker managed by this agent.

tlpAtsBreakerIndex.name: tlpAtsBreakerIndex
tlpAtsBreakerIndex.description: The table row index for the ats bank breaker.

tlpAtsBreakerStatus.name: tlpAtsBreakerStatus
tlpAtsBreakerStatus.description: Indicates whether the bank breaker is open(0), closed(1) or not installed(2).

tlpAtsHeatsinkTable.name: tlpAtsHeatsinkTable
tlpAtsHeatsinkTable.description: A list of ats heatsink thermistor table entries. The number of entries is given by the value of tlpAtsIdentNumHeatsinks.

tlpAtsHeatsinkEntry.name: tlpAtsHeatsinkEntry
tlpAtsHeatsinkEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular heatsink thermistor managed by this agent.

tlpAtsHeatsinkIndex.name: tlpAtsHeatsinkIndex
tlpAtsHeatsinkIndex.description: The table row index for the ats heatsink thermistor.

tlpAtsHeatsinkStatus.name: tlpAtsHeatsinkStatus
tlpAtsHeatsinkStatus.description: Indicates whether the heatsink thermistor is available. The entry will return notAvailable(0) if a thermistor is either non-existent or disconnected, or available(1) when connected.

tlpAtsHeatsinkTemperatureC.name: tlpAtsHeatsinkTemperatureC
tlpAtsHeatsinkTemperatureC.description: The temperature at the heatsink termistor in tenths degrees Centigrade. Heatsink temperature measurements are not supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsHeatsinkTemperatureF.name: tlpAtsHeatsinkTemperatureF
tlpAtsHeatsinkTemperatureF.description: The temperature at the heatsink termistor in tenths degrees Farenheit. Heatsink temperature measurements are not supported on all models. If not supported, this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsControlTable.name: tlpAtsControlTable
tlpAtsControlTable.description: The actionable controls for each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are atss.

tlpAtsControlEntry.name: tlpAtsControlEntry
tlpAtsControlEntry.description: An entry containing controls for a particular ats.

tlpAtsControlRamp.name: tlpAtsControlRamp
tlpAtsControlRamp.description: Set to TRUE to initiate the pre-designated ramp sequence on the ats.

tlpAtsControlShed.name: tlpAtsControlShed
tlpAtsControlShed.description: Set to TRUE to initiate the pre-designated shed sequence on the ats.

tlpAtsControlAtsOn.name: tlpAtsControlAtsOn
tlpAtsControlAtsOn.description: Set to TRUE to turn the ats on.

tlpAtsControlAtsOff.name: tlpAtsControlAtsOff
tlpAtsControlAtsOff.description: Set to TRUE to turn the ats off.

tlpAtsControlAtsReboot.name: tlpAtsControlAtsReboot
tlpAtsControlAtsReboot.description: Set to TRUE to reboot the ats.

tlpAtsControlResetGeneralFault.name: tlpAtsControlResetGeneralFault
tlpAtsControlResetGeneralFault.description: Set to TRUE to reset the general fault alarm indicated by tlpAtsDeviceGeneralFault.

tlpAtsConfigTable.name: tlpAtsConfigTable
tlpAtsConfigTable.description: The configuration options of each ats in device table. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are atss. Not all options are available on all atss.

tlpAtsConfigEntry.name: tlpAtsConfigEntry
tlpAtsConfigEntry.description: An entry containing configuration options for a particular ats.

tlpAtsConfigInputVoltage.name: tlpAtsConfigInputVoltage
tlpAtsConfigInputVoltage.description: The nominal value of the input line voltage. This value may not be supported on all models. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME. This value may not be writable on all models. If not writable, the value will be rejected and an appropriate error message will be returned.

tlpAtsConfigSourceSelect.name: tlpAtsConfigSourceSelect
tlpAtsConfigSourceSelect.description: The determination as to which of two AC input lines is designated as the primary input source. The other is designated as the secondary input source. This value will always return inputSourceA(1) for devices with a single input source. Setting this value is supported only on selected models.

tlpAtsConfigSource1ReturnTime.name: tlpAtsConfigSource1ReturnTime
tlpAtsConfigSource1ReturnTime.description: The nominal time to delay a transition to Source 1, if it is the preferred source.

tlpAtsConfigSource2ReturnTime.name: tlpAtsConfigSource2ReturnTime
tlpAtsConfigSource2ReturnTime.description: The nominal time to delay a transition to Source 2, if it is the preferred source.

tlpAtsConfigAutoRampOnTransition.name: tlpAtsConfigAutoRampOnTransition
tlpAtsConfigAutoRampOnTransition.description: When enabled(1), the ats should perform its preconfigured ramp sequence when the input source transfers from its designated secondary source to its designated primary source. This value not supported on all ats devices. If not supported, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigAutoShedOnTransition.name: tlpAtsConfigAutoShedOnTransition
tlpAtsConfigAutoShedOnTransition.description: When enabled(1), the ats should perform its preconfigured shed sequence when the input source transfers from its designated primary source to its designated secondary source. This value not supported on all ats devices. If not supported, then this value will always return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeTable.name: tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeTable
tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeTable.description: The voltage range options in this table is intended to configure the operating voltages of an ats. This is a sparse dependent table, and will contain some subset of devices that are atss. All voltage points defined in this table are listed in a specific order from high to low. All voltage points must satsify the conditions and ranges defined for each point. Any point violating any of the relative limits will be rejected. For optimal operation, it is recommended that tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageReset be set lower than tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageTransfer by a margin no less than 1% of tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageTransfer; and that tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferReset (tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferReset) be set higher than tlpAtsConfigSource1BrownoutSet (tlpAtsConfigSource2BrownoutSet) by a margin no less than 1% of tlpAtsConfigSource1BrownoutSet (tlpAtsConfigSource2BrownoutSet). *The upper limit of line voltage is tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound. The lower limit of line voltage is tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltageLowerBound. All minimum and maximum limits for each voltage point are all exlusive unless indicated otherwise.

tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeEntry.name: tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeEntry
tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeEntry.description: An entry containing voltage range configuration options for a particular ats.

tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageTransfer.name: tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageTransfer
tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageTransfer.description: The maximum line voltage allowed before the unit disconnects the AC input connection. The maximum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsInputHighTransferVoltageUpperBound (inclusively). The minimum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageReset. This value may not be configurable on all models. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageReset.name: tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageReset
tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageReset.description: If a unit is disconnected due to over-voltage, the line voltage has to fall below this value before the unit re-connects the AC input connection. The maximum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageTransfer. The minimum value allowed is dictated by the greater of tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferReset and tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferReset. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferReset.name: tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferReset
tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferReset.description: If input source 1 voltage level is above this value, a unit connected to source 2 will transition to source 1 (if it is the preferred source). The maximum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageReset. The minimum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigSource1BrownoutSet. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigSource1BrownoutSet.name: tlpAtsConfigSource1BrownoutSet
tlpAtsConfigSource1BrownoutSet.description: This value dictates the voltage level below which source 1 goes into a brown out condition. The maximum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferReset. The minimum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferSet. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferSet.name: tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferSet
tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferSet.description: If input source 1 voltage level falls below this value, a unit connected to source 1 will transition to source 2 (if it is in fair condition as denoted by tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferSet). The maximum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigSource1BrownoutSet. The minimum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageReset. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferReset.name: tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferReset
tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferReset.description: If input source 2 voltage level is above this value, a unit connected to source 1 will transition to source 2 (if it is the preferred source). The maximum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigHighVoltageReset. The minimum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigSource2BrownoutSet. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigSource2BrownoutSet.name: tlpAtsConfigSource2BrownoutSet
tlpAtsConfigSource2BrownoutSet.description: This value dictates the voltage level below which source 2 goes into a brown out condition. The maximum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferReset. The minimum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferSet. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferSet.name: tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferSet
tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferSet.description: If input source 2 voltage level falls below this value, a unit connected to source 2 will transition to source 1 (if it is in fair condition as denoted by tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferSet). The maximum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigSource2BrownoutSet. The minimum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageReset. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageReset.name: tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageReset
tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageReset.description: If a unit is disconnected due to under-voltage or is not powered up yet, the line voltage has to rise above this value before the unit gets connected to the AC input connection. The maximum value allowed is dictated by the lesser value of tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferSet and tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferSet. The minimum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageTransfer. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageTransfer.name: tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageTransfer
tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageTransfer.description: The minimum line voltage allowed before the unit disconnects the AC input connection. The maximum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageReset. The minimum value allowed is dictated by tlpAtsInputBadTransferVoltageLowerBound (inclusively). If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeLimitsTable.name: tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeLimitsTable
tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeLimitsTable.description: The voltage range table, as documented by tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeTable requires that all changes adhere with stack order, from high transfer voltage down to low transfer voltage. In addition to stack order, certain voltage range values have limits defining the absolute minimum and absolute maximum for such values. Any voltage value violating any respective limit defined herein will be rejected.

tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeLimitsEntry.name: tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeLimitsEntry
tlpAtsConfigVoltageRangeLimitsEntry.description: An entry containing voltage range limits configuration options for a particular ats.

tlpAtsConfigSourceBrownoutSetMinimum.name: tlpAtsConfigSourceBrownoutSetMinimum
tlpAtsConfigSourceBrownoutSetMinimum.description: This value dictates the absolute lower limit by which tlpAtsConfigSource1BrownoutSet and tlpAtsConfigSource2BrownoutSet can be set. tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferSet and tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferSet, respectively, are also used when determining the lowest value a brownout value can be set at any given time. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigSourceBrownoutSetMaximum.name: tlpAtsConfigSourceBrownoutSetMaximum
tlpAtsConfigSourceBrownoutSetMaximum.description: This value dictates the absolute upper limit by which tlpAtsConfigSource1BrownoutSet and tlpAtsConfigSource2BrownoutSet can be set. tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferReset and tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferReset, respectively, are also used when determining the greatest value a brownout value can be set at any given time. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigSourceTransferSetMinimum.name: tlpAtsConfigSourceTransferSetMinimum
tlpAtsConfigSourceTransferSetMinimum.description: This value dictates the absolute lower limit by which tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferSet and tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferSet can be set. tlpAtsConfigLowVoltageReset is also used when determining the lowest value a transferset value can be set at any given time. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAtsConfigSourceTransferSetMaximum.name: tlpAtsConfigSourceTransferSetMaximum
tlpAtsConfigSourceTransferSetMaximum.description: This value dictates the absolute upper limit by which tlpAtsConfigSource1TransferSet and tlpAtsConfigSource2TransferSet can be set. tlpAtsConfigSource1BrownoutSet and tlpAtsConfigSource2BrownoutSet, respectively, are also used when determining the greatest value a transferset value can be set at any given time. If not supported, this value will return ERROR_NO_SUCH_NAME.

tlpAgentConfigRemoteRegistration.name: tlpAgentConfigRemoteRegistration
tlpAgentConfigRemoteRegistration.description: Registers an SNMP contact's IP address and the port on which the contact is listening for SNMP traps. Setting this value is used to CREATE a table entry in a non-standard way. Getting this value will return a string INADDR_ANY and any port number. The port number should always be included. When unregistering an SNMP contact, the requester's IP address should be provided with a port number of 0. When setting or unsetting this OID, the IP address string should never be 0 nor should it be empty. The registration uses its default community string to register each contact. To use a community other than the default, then it must be appended to the end of the string delimited with a comma. The address should be of the format 0.0.0.0:00000 for IPv4. If IPv6 is supported, use the bracket-enclosed format given in IETF RFC 2732 Section 2, with the following examples: [FEDC:BA98:7654:3210:FEDC:BA98:7654:3210]:80 [1080:0:0:0:8:800:200C:417A]:162 [3ffe:2a00:100:7031::1]:162 [1080::8:800:200C:417A]:162,myCommunity [::192.9.5.5]:162,myCommunity [::FFFF:129.144.52.38]:80 [2010:836B:4179::836B:4179]:162

tlpAlarmTable.name: tlpAlarmTable
tlpAlarmTable.description: A list of alarm conditions for all devices managed by this agent. This table contains zero, one, or many rows at any moment, depending upon the number of alarm conditions in effect or conditions not acnowledged. The agent creates a row in the table each time a condition is detected and deletes that row when that condition no longer pertains (becomes inactive and is acknowledged). The agent creates the first row with tlpAlarmId equal to 1, and increments the value of tlpAlarmId each time a new row is created, wrapping to the first free value greater than or equal to 1 when the maximum value of tlpAlarmId would otherwise be exceeded. Consequently, after multiple operations, the table may become sparse (e.g., containing entries for rows 95, 100, 101, and 203) and the entries should not be assumed to be in chronological order because tlpAlarmId might have wrapped. The number of rows in the table at any given time is reflected by the value of tlpAlarmsPresent.

tlpAlarmEntry.name: tlpAlarmEntry
tlpAlarmEntry.description: An entry containing information application to a particular alarm.

tlpAlarmId.name: tlpAlarmId
tlpAlarmId.description: A unique identifier for an alarm condition. This value will remain constant for the duration of the alarm condition.

tlpAlarmDescr.name: tlpAlarmDescr
tlpAlarmDescr.description: A reference of the alarm description object. The object referenced should not be accessbile, but rather be used to provide a unique description for the alarm condition. The object referenced will be a well known alarm object associated with the device on which the alarm condition is active.

tlpAlarmTime.name: tlpAlarmTime
tlpAlarmTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the alarm condition was detected. If the alarm condition was detected at the time of agent startup and presumably existed before agent startup, the value of tlpAlarmsTime shall equal 0.

tlpAlarmTableRef.name: tlpAlarmTableRef
tlpAlarmTableRef.description: This value references the OID of a table object applicable to the alarm condition. This, in conjunction with the table row as defined by tlpAlarmTableRowRef, specifies the object/row within this table to which the alarm condition applies. Example 1 -- The following sample values will be returned for a UPS on battery: tlpAlarmId 28 tlpAlarmDescr tlpUpsAlarmOnBattery tlpAlarmTime 12345678 tlpAlarmTableRef tlpDeviceTable tlpAlarmTableRowRef tlpDeviceIndex.2 tlpAlarmDetail On Battery tlpAlarmType warning tlpAlarmState active tlpAlarmAcknowledged notAcknowledged In the above example, tlpAlarmTableRef references the device table and tlpAlarmTableRowRef references the 2nd managed device in that table. Example 2 -- The following sample values will be returned for a PDU with a load turned off: tlpAlarmId 46 tlpAlarmDescr tlpPduAlarmLoadOff tlpAlarmTime 12345678 tlpAlarmTableRef tlpPduOutletTable tlpAlarmTableRowRef tlpOutletIndex.1.4 tlpAlarmDetail Load Off tlpAlarmType warning tlpAlarmState active tlpAlarmAcknowledged acknowledged In the above example, tlpAlarmTableRef references the pdu outlet table and tlpAlarmTableRowRef references the 4th outlet on the 1st managed device.

tlpAlarmTableRowRef.name: tlpAlarmTableRowRef
tlpAlarmTableRowRef.description: This value is used in conjunction with tlpAlarmTableRef to define the object associated with this alarm condition. See the description of tlpAlarmTableRef for more information.

tlpAlarmDetail.name: tlpAlarmDetail
tlpAlarmDetail.description: A textual description of the alarm condition.

tlpAlarmState.name: tlpAlarmState
tlpAlarmState.description: The current state of this alarm condition. An active(1) alarm is a condition that currently exists. An inactive(2) alarm is a condition that no longer exists because the alarm either cleared or was resolved. Each alarm condition must be cleared and acknowledged before it is removed from this table (see tlpAlarmAcknowledged).

tlpAlarmAcknowledged.name: tlpAlarmAcknowledged
tlpAlarmAcknowledged.description: Denotes whether the alarm condition has been acknowledged. The agent will return notAcknowledged(1) if the condition has not been acknowledged, or acknowledged(2) when acknowledged. Writing the value acknowledged(2) for an alarm acknowledges the alarm condition. Each alarm condition must be cleared and acknowledged before it is removed from this table; therefore, even if acknowledged, the alarm will remain in this table until the alarm becomes inactive as denoted by tlpAlarmState.
